  15 """Faster R-CNN meta-architecture definition.
  16 
  17 General tensorflow implementation of Faster R-CNN detection models.
  18 
  19 See Faster R-CNN: Ren, Shaoqing, et al.
  20 "Faster R-CNN: Towards real-time object detection with region proposal
  21 networks." Advances in neural information processing systems. 2015.
  22 
  23 We allow for three modes: number_of_stages={1, 2, 3}. In case of 1 stage,
  24 all of the user facing methods (e.g., predict, postprocess, loss) can be used as
  25 if the model consisted only of the RPN, returning class agnostic proposals
  26 (these can be thought of as approximate detections with no associated class
  27 information).  In case of 2 stages, proposals are computed, then passed
  28 through a second stage "box classifier" to yield (multi-class) detections.
  29 Finally, in case of 3 stages which is only used during eval, proposals are
  30 computed, then passed through a second stage "box classifier" that will compute
  31 refined boxes and classes, and then features are pooled from the refined and
  32 non-maximum suppressed boxes and are passed through the box classifier again. If
  33 number of stages is 3 during training it will be reduced to two automatically.
  34 
  35 Implementations of Faster R-CNN models must define a new
  36 FasterRCNNFeatureExtractor and override three methods: `preprocess`,
  37 `_extract_proposal_features` (the first stage of the model), and
  38 `_extract_box_classifier_features` (the second stage of the model). Optionally,
  39 the `restore_fn` method can be overridden.  See tests for an example.
  40 
  41 A few important notes:
  42 + Batching conventions:  We support batched inference and training where
  43 all images within a batch have the same resolution.  Batch sizes are determined
  44 dynamically via the shape of the input tensors (rather than being specified
  45 directly as, e.g., a model constructor).
  46 
  47 A complication is that due to non-max suppression, we are not guaranteed to get
  48 the same number of proposals from the first stage RPN (region proposal network)
  49 for each image (though in practice, we should often get the same number of
  50 proposals).  For this reason we pad to a max number of proposals per image
  51 within a batch. This `self.max_num_proposals` property is set to the
  52 `first_stage_max_proposals` parameter at inference time and the
  53 `second_stage_batch_size` at training time since we subsample the batch to
  54 be sent through the box classifier during training.
  55 
  56 For the second stage of the pipeline, we arrange the proposals for all images
  57 within the batch along a single batch dimension.  For example, the input to
  58 _extract_box_classifier_features is a tensor of shape
  59 `[total_num_proposals, crop_height, crop_width, depth]` where
  60 total_num_proposals is batch_size * self.max_num_proposals.  (And note that per
  61 the above comment, a subset of these entries correspond to zero paddings.)
  62 
  63 + Coordinate representations:
  64 Following the API (see model.DetectionModel definition), our outputs after
  65 postprocessing operations are always normalized boxes however, internally, we
  66 sometimes convert to absolute --- e.g. for loss computation.  In particular,
  67 anchors and proposal_boxes are both represented as absolute coordinates.
  68 
  69 Images are resized in the `preprocess` method.
  70 
  71 The Faster R-CNN meta architecture has two post-processing methods
  72 `_postprocess_rpn` which is applied after first stage and
  73 `_postprocess_box_classifier` which is applied after second stage. There are
  74 three different ways post-processing can happen depending on number_of_stages
  75 configured in the meta architecture:
  76 
  77 1. When number_of_stages is 1:
  78   `_postprocess_rpn` is run as part of the `postprocess` method where
  79   true_image_shapes is used to clip proposals, perform non-max suppression and
  80   normalize them.
  81 2. When number of stages is 2:
  82   `_postprocess_rpn` is run as part of the `_predict_second_stage` method where
  83   `resized_image_shapes` is used to clip proposals, perform non-max suppression
  84   and normalize them. In this case `postprocess` method skips `_postprocess_rpn`
  85   and only runs `_postprocess_box_classifier` using `true_image_shapes` to clip
  86   detections, perform non-max suppression and normalize them.
  87 3. When number of stages is 3:
  88   `_postprocess_rpn` is run as part of the `_predict_second_stage` using
  89   `resized_image_shapes` to clip proposals, perform non-max suppression and
  90   normalize them. Subsequently, `_postprocess_box_classifier` is run as part of
  91   `_predict_third_stage` using `true_image_shapes` to clip detections, peform
  92   non-max suppression and normalize them. In this case, the `postprocess` method
  93   skips both `_postprocess_rpn` and `_postprocess_box_classifier`.
  94 """

 120 class FasterRCNNFeatureExtractor(object):
 121   """Faster R-CNN Feature Extractor definition."""
 122 
 123   def __init__(self,
 124                is_training,
 125                first_stage_features_stride,
 126                batch_norm_trainable=False,
 127                reuse_weights=None,
 128                weight_decay=0.0):
 129     """Constructor.
 130 
 131     Args:
 132       is_training: A boolean indicating whether the training version of the
 133         computation graph should be constructed.
 134       first_stage_features_stride: Output stride of extracted RPN feature map.
 135       batch_norm_trainable: Whether to update batch norm parameters during
 136         training or not. When training with a relative large batch size
 137         (e.g. 8), it could be desirable to enable batch norm update.
 138       reuse_weights: Whether to reuse variables. Default is None.
 139       weight_decay: float weight decay for feature extractor (default: 0.0).
 140     """
 141     self._is_training = is_training
 142     self._first_stage_features_stride = first_stage_features_stride
 143     self._train_batch_norm = (batch_norm_trainable and is_training)
 144     self._reuse_weights = tf.AUTO_REUSE if reuse_weights else None
 145     self._weight_decay = weight_decay
 146 
 147   @abc.abstractmethod
 148   def preprocess(self, resized_inputs):
 149     """Feature-extractor specific preprocessing (minus image resizing)."""
 150     pass
 151 
 152   def extract_proposal_features(self, preprocessed_inputs, scope):
 153     """Extracts first stage RPN features.
 154 
 155     This function is responsible for extracting feature maps from preprocessed
 156     images.  These features are used by the region proposal network (RPN) to
 157     predict proposals.
 158 
 159     Args:
 160       preprocessed_inputs: A [batch, height, width, channels] float tensor
 161         representing a batch of images.
 162       scope: A scope name.
 163 
 164     Returns:
 165       rpn_feature_map: A tensor with shape [batch, height, width, depth]
 166       activations: A dictionary mapping activation tensor names to tensors.
 167     """
 168     with tf.variable_scope(scope, values=[preprocessed_inputs]):
 169       return self._extract_proposal_features(preprocessed_inputs, scope)
 170 
 171   @abc.abstractmethod
 172   def _extract_proposal_features(self, preprocessed_inputs, scope):
 173     """Extracts first stage RPN features, to be overridden."""
 174     pass
 175 
 176   def extract_box_classifier_features(self, proposal_feature_maps, scope):
 177     """Extracts second stage box classifier features.
 178 
 179     Args:
 180       proposal_feature_maps: A 4-D float tensor with shape
 181         [batch_size * self.max_num_proposals, crop_height, crop_width, depth]
 182         representing the feature map cropped to each proposal.
 183       scope: A scope name.
 184 
 185     Returns:
 186       proposal_classifier_features: A 4-D float tensor with shape
 187         [batch_size * self.max_num_proposals, height, width, depth]
 188         representing box classifier features for each proposal.
 189     """
 190     with tf.variable_scope(
 191         scope, values=[proposal_feature_maps], reuse=tf.AUTO_REUSE):
 192       return self._extract_box_classifier_features(proposal_feature_maps, scope)
 193 
 194   @abc.abstractmethod
 195   def _extract_box_classifier_features(self, proposal_feature_maps, scope):
 196     """Extracts second stage box classifier features, to be overridden."""
 197     pass
 198 
 199   def restore_from_classification_checkpoint_fn(
 200       self,
 201       first_stage_feature_extractor_scope,
 202       second_stage_feature_extractor_scope):
 203     """Returns a map of variables to load from a foreign checkpoint.
 204 
 205     Args:
 206       first_stage_feature_extractor_scope: A scope name for the first stage
 207         feature extractor.
 208       second_stage_feature_extractor_scope: A scope name for the second stage
 209         feature extractor.
 210 
 211     Returns:
 212       A dict mapping variable names (to load from a checkpoint) to variables in
 213       the model graph.
 214     """
 215     variables_to_restore = {}
 216     for variable in variables_helper.get_global_variables_safely():
 217       for scope_name in [first_stage_feature_extractor_scope,
 218                          second_stage_feature_extractor_scope]:
 219         if variable.op.name.startswith(scope_name):
 220           var_name = variable.op.name.replace(scope_name + '/', '')
 221           variables_to_restore[var_name] = variable
 222     return variables_to_restore
 223

 225 class FasterRCNNKerasFeatureExtractor(object):
 226   """Keras-based Faster R-CNN Feature Extractor definition."""
 227 
 228   def __init__(self,
 229                is_training,
 230                first_stage_features_stride,
 231                batch_norm_trainable=False,
 232                weight_decay=0.0):
 233     """Constructor.
 234 
 235     Args:
 236       is_training: A boolean indicating whether the training version of the
 237         computation graph should be constructed.
 238       first_stage_features_stride: Output stride of extracted RPN feature map.
 239       batch_norm_trainable: Whether to update batch norm parameters during
 240         training or not. When training with a relative large batch size
 241         (e.g. 8), it could be desirable to enable batch norm update.
 242       weight_decay: float weight decay for feature extractor (default: 0.0).
 243     """
 244     self._is_training = is_training
 245     self._first_stage_features_stride = first_stage_features_stride
 246     self._train_batch_norm = (batch_norm_trainable and is_training)
 247     self._weight_decay = weight_decay
 248 
 249   @abc.abstractmethod
 250   def preprocess(self, resized_inputs):
 251     """Feature-extractor specific preprocessing (minus image resizing)."""
 252     pass
 253 
 254   @abc.abstractmethod
 255   def get_proposal_feature_extractor_model(self, name):
 256     """Get model that extracts first stage RPN features, to be overridden."""
 257     pass
 258 
 259   @abc.abstractmethod
 260   def get_box_classifier_feature_extractor_model(self, name):
 261     """Get model that extracts second stage box classifier features."""
 262     pass
 263 
 264   def restore_from_classification_checkpoint_fn(
 265       self,
 266       first_stage_feature_extractor_scope,
 267       second_stage_feature_extractor_scope):
 268     """Returns a map of variables to load from a foreign checkpoint.
 269 
 270     Args:
 271       first_stage_feature_extractor_scope: A scope name for the first stage
 272         feature extractor.
 273       second_stage_feature_extractor_scope: A scope name for the second stage
 274         feature extractor.
 275 
 276     Returns:
 277       A dict mapping variable names (to load from a checkpoint) to variables in
 278       the model graph.
 279     """
 280     variables_to_restore = {}
 281     for variable in variables_helper.get_global_variables_safely():
 282       for scope_name in [first_stage_feature_extractor_scope,
 283                          second_stage_feature_extractor_scope]:
 284         if variable.op.name.startswith(scope_name):
 285           var_name = variable.op.name.replace(scope_name + '/', '')
 286           variables_to_restore[var_name] = variable
 287     return variables_to_restore

 290 class FasterRCNNMetaArch(model.DetectionModel):
 291   """Faster R-CNN Meta-architecture definition."""
 292 
 293   def __init__(self,
 294                is_training,
 295                num_classes,
 296                image_resizer_fn,
 297                feature_extractor,
 298                number_of_stages,
 299                first_stage_anchor_generator,
 300                first_stage_target_assigner,
 301                first_stage_atrous_rate,
 302                first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn,
 303                first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size,
 304                first_stage_box_predictor_depth,
 305                first_stage_minibatch_size,
 306                first_stage_sampler,
 307                first_stage_non_max_suppression_fn,
 308                first_stage_max_proposals,
 309                first_stage_localization_loss_weight,
 310                first_stage_objectness_loss_weight,
 311                crop_and_resize_fn,
 312                initial_crop_size,
 313                maxpool_kernel_size,
 314                maxpool_stride,
 315                second_stage_target_assigner,
 316                second_stage_mask_rcnn_box_predictor,
 317                second_stage_batch_size,
 318                second_stage_sampler,
 319                second_stage_non_max_suppression_fn,
 320                second_stage_score_conversion_fn,
 321                second_stage_localization_loss_weight,
 322                second_stage_classification_loss_weight,
 323                second_stage_classification_loss,
 324                second_stage_mask_prediction_loss_weight=1.0,
 325                hard_example_miner=None,
 326                parallel_iterations=16,
 327                add_summaries=True,
 328                clip_anchors_to_image=False,
 329                use_static_shapes=False,
 330                resize_masks=True,
 331                freeze_batchnorm=False,
 332                return_raw_detections_during_predict=False,
 333                output_final_box_features=False):
 334     """FasterRCNNMetaArch Constructor.
 335 
 336     Args:
 337       is_training: A boolean indicating whether the training version of the
 338         computation graph should be constructed.
 339       num_classes: Number of classes.  Note that num_classes *does not*
 340         include the background category, so if groundtruth labels take values
 341         in {0, 1, .., K-1}, num_classes=K (and not K+1, even though the
 342         assigned classification targets can range from {0,... K}).
 343       image_resizer_fn: A callable for image resizing.  This callable
 344         takes a rank-3 image tensor of shape [height, width, channels]
 345         (corresponding to a single image), an optional rank-3 instance mask
 346         tensor of shape [num_masks, height, width] and returns a resized rank-3
 347         image tensor, a resized mask tensor if one was provided in the input. In
 348         addition this callable must also return a 1-D tensor of the form
 349         [height, width, channels] containing the size of the true image, as the
 350         image resizer can perform zero padding. See protos/image_resizer.proto.
 351       feature_extractor: A FasterRCNNFeatureExtractor object.
 352       number_of_stages:  An integer values taking values in {1, 2, 3}. If
 353         1, the function will construct only the Region Proposal Network (RPN)
 354         part of the model. If 2, the function will perform box refinement and
 355         other auxiliary predictions all in the second stage. If 3, it will
 356         extract features from refined boxes and perform the auxiliary
 357         predictions on the non-maximum suppressed refined boxes.
 358         If is_training is true and the value of number_of_stages is 3, it is
 359         reduced to 2 since all the model heads are trained in parallel in second
 360         stage during training.
 361       first_stage_anchor_generator: An anchor_generator.AnchorGenerator object
 362         (note that currently we only support
 363         grid_anchor_generator.GridAnchorGenerator objects)
 364       first_stage_target_assigner: Target assigner to use for first stage of
 365         Faster R-CNN (RPN).
 366       first_stage_atrous_rate: A single integer indicating the atrous rate for
 367         the single convolution op which is applied to the `rpn_features_to_crop`
 368         tensor to obtain a tensor to be used for box prediction. Some feature
 369         extractors optionally allow for producing feature maps computed at
 370         denser resolutions.  The atrous rate is used to compensate for the
 371         denser feature maps by using an effectively larger receptive field.
 372         (This should typically be set to 1).
 373       first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn: Either a
 374         Keras layer hyperparams object or a function to construct tf-slim
 375         arg_scope for conv2d, separable_conv2d and fully_connected ops. Used
 376         for the RPN box predictor. If it is a keras hyperparams object the
 377         RPN box predictor will be a Keras model. If it is a function to
 378         construct an arg scope it will be a tf-slim box predictor.
 379       first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size: Kernel size to use for the
 380         convolution op just prior to RPN box predictions.
 381       first_stage_box_predictor_depth: Output depth for the convolution op
 382         just prior to RPN box predictions.
 383       first_stage_minibatch_size: The "batch size" to use for computing the
 384         objectness and location loss of the region proposal network. This
 385         "batch size" refers to the number of anchors selected as contributing
 386         to the loss function for any given image within the image batch and is
 387         only called "batch_size" due to terminology from the Faster R-CNN paper.
 388       first_stage_sampler: Sampler to use for first stage loss (RPN loss).
 389       first_stage_non_max_suppression_fn: batch_multiclass_non_max_suppression
 390         callable that takes `boxes`, `scores` and optional `clip_window`(with
 391         all other inputs already set) and returns a dictionary containing
 392         tensors with keys: `detection_boxes`, `detection_scores`,
 393         `detection_classes`, `num_detections`. This is used to perform non max
 394         suppression  on the boxes predicted by the Region Proposal Network
 395         (RPN).
 396         See `post_processing.batch_multiclass_non_max_suppression` for the type
 397         and shape of these tensors.
 398       first_stage_max_proposals: Maximum number of boxes to retain after
 399         performing Non-Max Suppression (NMS) on the boxes predicted by the
 400         Region Proposal Network (RPN).
 401       first_stage_localization_loss_weight: A float
 402       first_stage_objectness_loss_weight: A float
 403       crop_and_resize_fn: A differentiable resampler to use for cropping RPN
 404         proposal features.
 405       initial_crop_size: A single integer indicating the output size
 406         (width and height are set to be the same) of the initial bilinear
 407         interpolation based cropping during ROI pooling.
 408       maxpool_kernel_size: A single integer indicating the kernel size of the
 409         max pool op on the cropped feature map during ROI pooling.
 410       maxpool_stride: A single integer indicating the stride of the max pool
 411         op on the cropped feature map during ROI pooling.
 412       second_stage_target_assigner: Target assigner to use for second stage of
 413         Faster R-CNN. If the model is configured with multiple prediction heads,
 414         this target assigner is used to generate targets for all heads (with the
 415         correct `unmatched_class_label`).
 416       second_stage_mask_rcnn_box_predictor: Mask R-CNN box predictor to use for
 417         the second stage.
 418       second_stage_batch_size: The batch size used for computing the
 419         classification and refined location loss of the box classifier.  This
 420         "batch size" refers to the number of proposals selected as contributing
 421         to the loss function for any given image within the image batch and is
 422         only called "batch_size" due to terminology from the Faster R-CNN paper.
 423       second_stage_sampler:  Sampler to use for second stage loss (box
 424         classifier loss).
 425       second_stage_non_max_suppression_fn: batch_multiclass_non_max_suppression
 426         callable that takes `boxes`, `scores`, optional `clip_window` and
 427         optional (kwarg) `mask` inputs (with all other inputs already set)
 428         and returns a dictionary containing tensors with keys:
 429         `detection_boxes`, `detection_scores`, `detection_classes`,
 430         `num_detections`, and (optionally) `detection_masks`. See
 431         `post_processing.batch_multiclass_non_max_suppression` for the type and
 432         shape of these tensors.
 433       second_stage_score_conversion_fn: Callable elementwise nonlinearity
 434         (that takes tensors as inputs and returns tensors).  This is usually
 435         used to convert logits to probabilities.
 436       second_stage_localization_loss_weight: A float indicating the scale factor
 437         for second stage localization loss.
 438       second_stage_classification_loss_weight: A float indicating the scale
 439         factor for second stage classification loss.
 440       second_stage_classification_loss: Classification loss used by the second
 441         stage classifier. Either losses.WeightedSigmoidClassificationLoss or
 442         losses.WeightedSoftmaxClassificationLoss.
 443       second_stage_mask_prediction_loss_weight: A float indicating the scale
 444         factor for second stage mask prediction loss. This is applicable only if
 445         second stage box predictor is configured to predict masks.
 446       hard_example_miner:  A losses.HardExampleMiner object (can be None).
 447       parallel_iterations: (Optional) The number of iterations allowed to run
 448         in parallel for calls to tf.map_fn.
 449       add_summaries: boolean (default: True) controlling whether summary ops
 450         should be added to tensorflow graph.
 451       clip_anchors_to_image: Normally, anchors generated for a given image size
 452         are pruned during training if they lie outside the image window. This
 453         option clips the anchors to be within the image instead of pruning.
 454       use_static_shapes: If True, uses implementation of ops with static shape
 455         guarantees.
 456       resize_masks: Indicates whether the masks presend in the groundtruth
 457         should be resized in the model with `image_resizer_fn`
 458       freeze_batchnorm: Whether to freeze batch norm parameters in the first
 459         stage box predictor during training or not. When training with a small
 460         batch size (e.g. 1), it is desirable to freeze batch norm update and
 461         use pretrained batch norm params.
 462       return_raw_detections_during_predict: Whether to return raw detection
 463         boxes in the predict() method. These are decoded boxes that have not
 464         been through postprocessing (i.e. NMS). Default False.
 465       output_final_box_features: Whether to output final box features. If true,
 466         it crops the feauture map based on the final box prediction and returns
 467         in the dict as detection_features.
 468 
 469     Raises:
 470       ValueError: If `second_stage_batch_size` > `first_stage_max_proposals` at
 471         training time.
 472       ValueError: If first_stage_anchor_generator is not of type
 473         grid_anchor_generator.GridAnchorGenerator.
 474     """
 475     # TODO(rathodv): add_summaries is currently unused. Respect that directive
 476     # in the future.
 477     super(FasterRCNNMetaArch, self).__init__(num_classes=num_classes)
 478 
 479     if not isinstance(first_stage_anchor_generator,
 480                       grid_anchor_generator.GridAnchorGenerator):
 481       raise ValueError('first_stage_anchor_generator must be of type '
 482                        'grid_anchor_generator.GridAnchorGenerator.')
 483 
 484     self._is_training = is_training
 485     self._image_resizer_fn = image_resizer_fn
 486     self._resize_masks = resize_masks
 487     self._feature_extractor = feature_extractor
 488     if isinstance(feature_extractor, FasterRCNNKerasFeatureExtractor):
 489       # We delay building the feature extractor until it is used,
 490       # to avoid creating the variables when a model is built just for data
 491       # preprocessing. (This prevents a subtle bug where variable names are
 492       # mismatched across workers, causing only one worker to be able to train)
 493       self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features = (
 494           _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR)
 495       self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features = (
 496           _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR)
 497     else:
 498       self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features = None
 499       self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features = None
 500 
 501     self._number_of_stages = number_of_stages
 502 
 503     self._proposal_target_assigner = first_stage_target_assigner
 504     self._detector_target_assigner = second_stage_target_assigner
 505     # Both proposal and detector target assigners use the same box coder
 506     self._box_coder = self._proposal_target_assigner.box_coder
 507 
 508     # (First stage) Region proposal network parameters
 509     self._first_stage_anchor_generator = first_stage_anchor_generator
 510     self._first_stage_atrous_rate = first_stage_atrous_rate
 511     self._first_stage_box_predictor_depth = first_stage_box_predictor_depth
 512     self._first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size = (
 513         first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size)
 514     self._first_stage_minibatch_size = first_stage_minibatch_size
 515     self._first_stage_sampler = first_stage_sampler
 516     if isinstance(first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn,
 517                   hyperparams_builder.KerasLayerHyperparams):
 518       num_anchors_per_location = (
 519           self._first_stage_anchor_generator.num_anchors_per_location())
 520       if len(num_anchors_per_location) != 1:
 521         raise ValueError('anchor_generator is expected to generate anchors '
 522                          'corresponding to a single feature map.')
 523       conv_hyperparams = (
 524           first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn)
 525       self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv = (
 526           tf.keras.Sequential([
 527               tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(
 528                   self._first_stage_box_predictor_depth,
 529                   kernel_size=[self._first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size,
 530                                self._first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size],
 531                   dilation_rate=self._first_stage_atrous_rate,
 532                   padding='SAME',
 533                   name='RPNConv',
 534                   **conv_hyperparams.params()),
 535               conv_hyperparams.build_batch_norm(
 536                   (self._is_training and not freeze_batchnorm),
 537                   name='RPNBatchNorm'),
 538               tf.keras.layers.Lambda(
 539                   tf.nn.relu6,
 540                   name='RPNActivation')
 541           ], name='FirstStageRPNFeatures'))
 542       self._first_stage_box_predictor = (
 543           box_predictor_builder.build_convolutional_keras_box_predictor(
 544               is_training=self._is_training,
 545               num_classes=1,
 546               conv_hyperparams=conv_hyperparams,
 547               freeze_batchnorm=freeze_batchnorm,
 548               inplace_batchnorm_update=False,
 549               num_predictions_per_location_list=num_anchors_per_location,
 550               use_dropout=False,
 551               dropout_keep_prob=1.0,
 552               box_code_size=self._box_coder.code_size,
 553               kernel_size=1,
 554               num_layers_before_predictor=0,
 555               min_depth=0,
 556               max_depth=0,
 557               name=self.first_stage_box_predictor_scope))
 558     else:
 559       self._first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn = (
 560           first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn)
 561       def rpn_box_predictor_feature_extractor(rpn_features_to_crop):
 562         with slim.arg_scope(self._first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn()):
 563           reuse = tf.get_variable_scope().reuse
 564           return slim.conv2d(
 565               rpn_features_to_crop,
 566               self._first_stage_box_predictor_depth,
 567               kernel_size=[
 568                   self._first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size,
 569                   self._first_stage_box_predictor_kernel_size
 570               ],
 571               rate=self._first_stage_atrous_rate,
 572               activation_fn=tf.nn.relu6,
 573               scope='Conv',
 574               reuse=reuse)
 575       self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv = (
 576           rpn_box_predictor_feature_extractor)
 577       self._first_stage_box_predictor = (
 578           box_predictor_builder.build_convolutional_box_predictor(
 579               is_training=self._is_training,
 580               num_classes=1,
 581               conv_hyperparams_fn=self._first_stage_box_predictor_arg_scope_fn,
 582               use_dropout=False,
 583               dropout_keep_prob=1.0,
 584               box_code_size=self._box_coder.code_size,
 585               kernel_size=1,
 586               num_layers_before_predictor=0,
 587               min_depth=0,
 588               max_depth=0))
 589 
 590     self._first_stage_nms_fn = first_stage_non_max_suppression_fn
 591     self._first_stage_max_proposals = first_stage_max_proposals
 592     self._use_static_shapes = use_static_shapes
 593 
 594     self._first_stage_localization_loss = (
 595         losses.WeightedSmoothL1LocalizationLoss())
 596     self._first_stage_objectness_loss = (
 597         losses.WeightedSoftmaxClassificationLoss())
 598     self._first_stage_loc_loss_weight = first_stage_localization_loss_weight
 599     self._first_stage_obj_loss_weight = first_stage_objectness_loss_weight
 600 
 601     # Per-region cropping parameters
 602     self._crop_and_resize_fn = crop_and_resize_fn
 603     self._initial_crop_size = initial_crop_size
 604     self._maxpool_kernel_size = maxpool_kernel_size
 605     self._maxpool_stride = maxpool_stride
 606     # If max pooling is to be used, build the layer
 607     if maxpool_kernel_size:
 608       self._maxpool_layer = tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(
 609           [self._maxpool_kernel_size, self._maxpool_kernel_size],
 610           strides=self._maxpool_stride,
 611           name='MaxPool2D')
 612 
 613     self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor = second_stage_mask_rcnn_box_predictor
 614 
 615     self._second_stage_batch_size = second_stage_batch_size
 616     self._second_stage_sampler = second_stage_sampler
 617 
 618     self._second_stage_nms_fn = second_stage_non_max_suppression_fn
 619     self._second_stage_score_conversion_fn = second_stage_score_conversion_fn
 620 
 621     self._second_stage_localization_loss = (
 622         losses.WeightedSmoothL1LocalizationLoss())
 623     self._second_stage_classification_loss = second_stage_classification_loss
 624     self._second_stage_mask_loss = (
 625         losses.WeightedSigmoidClassificationLoss())
 626     self._second_stage_loc_loss_weight = second_stage_localization_loss_weight
 627     self._second_stage_cls_loss_weight = second_stage_classification_loss_weight
 628     self._second_stage_mask_loss_weight = (
 629         second_stage_mask_prediction_loss_weight)
 630     self._hard_example_miner = hard_example_miner
 631     self._parallel_iterations = parallel_iterations
 632 
 633     self.clip_anchors_to_image = clip_anchors_to_image
 634 
 635     if self._number_of_stages <= 0 or self._number_of_stages > 3:
 636       raise ValueError('Number of stages should be a value in {1, 2, 3}.')
 637     self._batched_prediction_tensor_names = []
 638     self._return_raw_detections_during_predict = (
 639         return_raw_detections_during_predict)
 640     self._output_final_box_features = output_final_box_features

 658   @property

 661

 663     example miner is not configured, else it is set to
 664     `first_stage_max_proposals`. At inference time, this is always set to
 665     `first_stage_max_proposals`.

 693   def preprocess(self, inputs):
 694     """Feature-extractor specific preprocessing.
 695 
 696     See base class.
 697 
 698     For Faster R-CNN, we perform image resizing in the base class --- each
 699     class subclassing FasterRCNNMetaArch is responsible for any additional
 700     preprocessing (e.g., scaling pixel values to be in [-1, 1]).
 701 
 702     Args:
 703       inputs: a [batch, height_in, width_in, channels] float tensor representing
 704         a batch of images with values between 0 and 255.0.
 705 
 706     Returns:
 707       preprocessed_inputs: a [batch, height_out, width_out, channels] float
 708         tensor representing a batch of images.
 709       true_image_shapes: int32 tensor of shape [batch, 3] where each row is
 710         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
 711         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
 712         with zeros.
 713     Raises:
 714       ValueError: if inputs tensor does not have type tf.float32
 715     """
 716 
 717     with tf.name_scope('Preprocessor'):
 718       (resized_inputs,
 719        true_image_shapes) = shape_utils.resize_images_and_return_shapes(
 720            inputs, self._image_resizer_fn)
 721 
 722       return (self._feature_extractor.preprocess(resized_inputs),
 723               true_image_shapes)
 724 
 725   def _compute_clip_window(self, image_shapes):
 726     """Computes clip window for non max suppression based on image shapes.
 727 
 728     This function assumes that the clip window's left top corner is at (0, 0).
 729 
 730     Args:
 731       image_shapes: A 2-D int32 tensor of shape [batch_size, 3] containing
 732       shapes of images in the batch. Each row represents [height, width,
 733       channels] of an image.
 734 
 735     Returns:
 736       A 2-D float32 tensor of shape [batch_size, 4] containing the clip window
 737       for each image in the form [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax].
 738     """
 739     clip_heights = image_shapes[:, 0]
 740     clip_widths = image_shapes[:, 1]
 741     clip_window = tf.cast(
 742         tf.stack([
 743             tf.zeros_like(clip_heights),
 744             tf.zeros_like(clip_heights), clip_heights, clip_widths
 745         ],
 746                  axis=1),
 747         dtype=tf.float32)
 748     return clip_window
 749 
 750   def _proposal_postprocess(self, rpn_box_encodings,
 751                             rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background, anchors,
 752                             image_shape, true_image_shapes):
 753     """Wraps over FasterRCNNMetaArch._postprocess_rpn()."""
 754     image_shape_2d = self._image_batch_shape_2d(image_shape)
 755     proposal_boxes_normalized, _, _, num_proposals, _, _ = \
 756         self._postprocess_rpn(
 757             rpn_box_encodings, rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background,
 758             anchors, image_shape_2d, true_image_shapes)
 759     return proposal_boxes_normalized, num_proposals
 760 
 761   def predict(self, preprocessed_inputs, true_image_shapes, **side_inputs):
 762     """Predicts unpostprocessed tensors from input tensor.
 763 
 764     This function takes an input batch of images and runs it through the
 765     forward pass of the network to yield "raw" un-postprocessed predictions.
 766     If `number_of_stages` is 1, this function only returns first stage
 767     RPN predictions (un-postprocessed).  Otherwise it returns both
 768     first stage RPN predictions as well as second stage box classifier
 769     predictions.
 770 
 771     Other remarks:
 772     + Anchor pruning vs. clipping: following the recommendation of the Faster
 773     R-CNN paper, we prune anchors that venture outside the image window at
 774     training time and clip anchors to the image window at inference time.
 775     + Proposal padding: as described at the top of the file, proposals are
 776     padded to self._max_num_proposals and flattened so that proposals from all
 777     images within the input batch are arranged along the same batch dimension.
 778 
 779     Args:
 780       preprocessed_inputs: a [batch, height, width, channels] float tensor
 781         representing a batch of images.
 782       true_image_shapes: int32 tensor of shape [batch, 3] where each row is
 783         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
 784         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
 785         with zeros.
 786       **side_inputs: additional tensors that are required by the network.
 787 
 788     Returns:
 789       prediction_dict: a dictionary holding "raw" prediction tensors:
 790         1) rpn_box_predictor_features: A 4-D float32 tensor with shape
 791           [batch_size, height, width, depth] to be used for predicting proposal
 792           boxes and corresponding objectness scores.
 793         2) rpn_features_to_crop: A 4-D float32 tensor with shape
 794           [batch_size, height, width, depth] representing image features to crop
 795           using the proposal boxes predicted by the RPN.
 796         3) image_shape: a 1-D tensor of shape [4] representing the input
 797           image shape.
 798         4) rpn_box_encodings:  3-D float tensor of shape
 799           [batch_size, num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
 800           predicted boxes.
 801         5) rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background: 3-D float tensor of shape
 802           [batch_size, num_anchors, 2] containing class
 803           predictions (logits) for each of the anchors.  Note that this
 804           tensor *includes* background class predictions (at class index 0).
 805         6) anchors: A 2-D tensor of shape [num_anchors, 4] representing anchors
 806           for the first stage RPN (in absolute coordinates).  Note that
 807           `num_anchors` can differ depending on whether the model is created in
 808           training or inference mode.
 809         7) feature_maps: A single element list containing a 4-D float32 tensor
 810           with shape batch_size, height, width, depth] representing the RPN
 811           features to crop.
 812 
 813         (and if number_of_stages > 1):
 814         8) refined_box_encodings: a 3-D tensor with shape
 815           [total_num_proposals, num_classes, self._box_coder.code_size]
 816           representing predicted (final) refined box encodings, where
 817           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals. If using
 818           a shared box across classes the shape will instead be
 819           [total_num_proposals, 1, self._box_coder.code_size].
 820         9) class_predictions_with_background: a 3-D tensor with shape
 821           [total_num_proposals, num_classes + 1] containing class
 822           predictions (logits) for each of the anchors, where
 823           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals.
 824           Note that this tensor *includes* background class predictions
 825           (at class index 0).
 826         10) num_proposals: An int32 tensor of shape [batch_size] representing
 827           the number of proposals generated by the RPN.  `num_proposals` allows
 828           us to keep track of which entries are to be treated as zero paddings
 829           and which are not since we always pad the number of proposals to be
 830           `self.max_num_proposals` for each image.
 831         11) proposal_boxes: A float32 tensor of shape
 832           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing
 833           decoded proposal bounding boxes in absolute coordinates.
 834         12) mask_predictions: (optional) a 4-D tensor with shape
 835           [total_num_padded_proposals, num_classes, mask_height, mask_width]
 836           containing instance mask predictions.
 837         13) raw_detection_boxes: (optional) a
 838           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, num_classes, 4] float32 tensor
 839           with detections prior to NMS in normalized coordinates.
 840         14) raw_detection_feature_map_indices: (optional) a
 841           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, num_classes] int32 tensor with
 842           indices indicating which feature map each raw detection box was
 843           produced from. The indices correspond to the elements in the
 844           'feature_maps' field.
 845 
 846     Raises:
 847       ValueError: If `predict` is called before `preprocess`.
 848     """
 849     prediction_dict = self._predict_first_stage(preprocessed_inputs)
 850 
 851     if self._number_of_stages >= 2:
 852       prediction_dict.update(
 853           self._predict_second_stage(
 854               prediction_dict['rpn_box_encodings'],
 855               prediction_dict['rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background'],
 856               prediction_dict['rpn_features_to_crop'],
 857               prediction_dict['anchors'], prediction_dict['image_shape'],
 858               true_image_shapes, **side_inputs))
 859 
 860     if self._number_of_stages == 3:
 861       prediction_dict = self._predict_third_stage(prediction_dict,
 862                                                   true_image_shapes)
 863 
 864     self._batched_prediction_tensor_names = [
 865         x for x in prediction_dict if x not in ('image_shape', 'anchors')
 866     ]
 867     return prediction_dict
 868 
 869   def _predict_first_stage(self, preprocessed_inputs):
 870     """First stage of prediction.
 871 
 872     Args:
 873       preprocessed_inputs: a [batch, height, width, channels] float tensor
 874         representing a batch of images.
 875 
 876     Returns:
 877       prediction_dict: a dictionary holding "raw" prediction tensors:
 878         1) rpn_box_predictor_features: A 4-D float32/bfloat16 tensor with shape
 879           [batch_size, height, width, depth] to be used for predicting proposal
 880           boxes and corresponding objectness scores.
 881         2) rpn_features_to_crop: A 4-D float32/bfloat16 tensor with shape
 882           [batch_size, height, width, depth] representing image features to crop
 883           using the proposal boxes predicted by the RPN.
 884         3) image_shape: a 1-D tensor of shape [4] representing the input
 885           image shape.
 886         4) rpn_box_encodings:  3-D float32 tensor of shape
 887           [batch_size, num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
 888           predicted boxes.
 889         5) rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background: 3-D float32 tensor of
 890           shape [batch_size, num_anchors, 2] containing class predictions
 891           (logits) for each of the anchors.  Note that this tensor *includes*
 892           background class predictions (at class index 0).
 893         6) anchors: A 2-D tensor of shape [num_anchors, 4] representing anchors
 894           for the first stage RPN (in absolute coordinates).  Note that
 895           `num_anchors` can differ depending on whether the model is created in
 896           training or inference mode.
 897         7) feature_maps: A single element list containing a 4-D float32 tensor
 898           with shape batch_size, height, width, depth] representing the RPN
 899           features to crop.
 900     """
 901     (rpn_box_predictor_features, rpn_features_to_crop, anchors_boxlist,
 902      image_shape) = self._extract_rpn_feature_maps(preprocessed_inputs)
 903     (rpn_box_encodings, rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background
 904     ) = self._predict_rpn_proposals(rpn_box_predictor_features)
 905 
 906     # The Faster R-CNN paper recommends pruning anchors that venture outside
 907     # the image window at training time and clipping at inference time.
 908     clip_window = tf.cast(tf.stack([0, 0, image_shape[1], image_shape[2]]),
 909                           dtype=tf.float32)
 910     if self._is_training:
 911       if self.clip_anchors_to_image:
 912         anchors_boxlist = box_list_ops.clip_to_window(
 913             anchors_boxlist, clip_window, filter_nonoverlapping=False)
 914       else:
 915         (rpn_box_encodings, rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background,
 916          anchors_boxlist) = self._remove_invalid_anchors_and_predictions(
 917              rpn_box_encodings, rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background,
 918              anchors_boxlist, clip_window)
 919     else:
 920       anchors_boxlist = box_list_ops.clip_to_window(
 921           anchors_boxlist, clip_window,
 922           filter_nonoverlapping=not self._use_static_shapes)
 923 
 924     self._anchors = anchors_boxlist
 925     prediction_dict = {
 926         'rpn_box_predictor_features':
 927             rpn_box_predictor_features,
 928         'rpn_features_to_crop':
 929             rpn_features_to_crop,
 930         'image_shape':
 931             image_shape,
 932         'rpn_box_encodings':
 933             tf.cast(rpn_box_encodings, dtype=tf.float32),
 934         'rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background':
 935             tf.cast(rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background,
 936                     dtype=tf.float32),
 937         'anchors':
 938             anchors_boxlist.data['boxes'],
 939         fields.PredictionFields.feature_maps: [rpn_features_to_crop]
 940     }
 941     return prediction_dict
 942 
 943   def _image_batch_shape_2d(self, image_batch_shape_1d):
 944     """Takes a 1-D image batch shape tensor and converts it to a 2-D tensor.
 945 
 946     Example:
 947     If 1-D image batch shape tensor is [2, 300, 300, 3]. The corresponding 2-D
 948     image batch tensor would be [[300, 300, 3], [300, 300, 3]]
 949 
 950     Args:
 951       image_batch_shape_1d: 1-D tensor of the form [batch_size, height,
 952         width, channels].
 953 
 954     Returns:
 955       image_batch_shape_2d: 2-D tensor of shape [batch_size, 3] were each row is
 956         of the form [height, width, channels].
 957     """
 958     return tf.tile(tf.expand_dims(image_batch_shape_1d[1:], 0),
 959                    [image_batch_shape_1d[0], 1])
 960 
 961   def _predict_second_stage(self, rpn_box_encodings,
 962                             rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background,
 963                             rpn_features_to_crop, anchors, image_shape,
 964                             true_image_shapes, **side_inputs):
 965     """Predicts the output tensors from second stage of Faster R-CNN.
 966 
 967     Args:
 968       rpn_box_encodings: 3-D float tensor of shape
 969         [batch_size, num_valid_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
 970         predicted boxes.
 971       rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background: 2-D float tensor of shape
 972         [batch_size, num_valid_anchors, 2] containing class
 973         predictions (logits) for each of the anchors.  Note that this
 974         tensor *includes* background class predictions (at class index 0).
 975       rpn_features_to_crop: A 4-D float32 or bfloat16 tensor with shape
 976         [batch_size, height, width, depth] representing image features to crop
 977         using the proposal boxes predicted by the RPN.
 978       anchors: 2-D float tensor of shape
 979         [num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size].
 980       image_shape: A 1D int32 tensors of size [4] containing the image shape.
 981       true_image_shapes: int32 tensor of shape [batch, 3] where each row is
 982         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
 983         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
 984         with zeros.
 985       **side_inputs: additional tensors that are required by the network.
 986 
 987     Returns:
 988       prediction_dict: a dictionary holding "raw" prediction tensors:
 989         1) refined_box_encodings: a 3-D float32 tensor with shape
 990           [total_num_proposals, num_classes, self._box_coder.code_size]
 991           representing predicted (final) refined box encodings, where
 992           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals. If using a
 993           shared box across classes the shape will instead be
 994           [total_num_proposals, 1, self._box_coder.code_size].
 995         2) class_predictions_with_background: a 3-D float32 tensor with shape
 996           [total_num_proposals, num_classes + 1] containing class
 997           predictions (logits) for each of the anchors, where
 998           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals.
 999           Note that this tensor *includes* background class predictions
1000           (at class index 0).
1001         3) num_proposals: An int32 tensor of shape [batch_size] representing the
1002           number of proposals generated by the RPN.  `num_proposals` allows us
1003           to keep track of which entries are to be treated as zero paddings and
1004           which are not since we always pad the number of proposals to be
1005           `self.max_num_proposals` for each image.
1006         4) proposal_boxes: A float32 tensor of shape
1007           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing
1008           decoded proposal bounding boxes in absolute coordinates.
1009         5) proposal_boxes_normalized: A float32 tensor of shape
1010           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing decoded proposal
1011           bounding boxes in normalized coordinates. Can be used to override the
1012           boxes proposed by the RPN, thus enabling one to extract features and
1013           get box classification and prediction for externally selected areas
1014           of the image.
1015         6) box_classifier_features: a 4-D float32/bfloat16 tensor
1016           representing the features for each proposal.
1017         If self._return_raw_detections_during_predict is True, the dictionary
1018         will also contain:
1019         7) raw_detection_boxes: a 4-D float32 tensor with shape
1020           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, num_classes, 4] in normalized
1021           coordinates.
1022         8) raw_detection_feature_map_indices: a 3-D int32 tensor with shape
1023           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, num_classes].
1024     """
1025     proposal_boxes_normalized, num_proposals = self._proposal_postprocess(
1026         rpn_box_encodings, rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background, anchors,
1027         image_shape, true_image_shapes)
1028     prediction_dict = self._box_prediction(rpn_features_to_crop,
1029                                            proposal_boxes_normalized,
1030                                            image_shape, true_image_shapes,
1031                                            **side_inputs)
1032     prediction_dict['num_proposals'] = num_proposals
1033     return prediction_dict
1034 
1035   def _box_prediction(self, rpn_features_to_crop, proposal_boxes_normalized,
1036                       image_shape, true_image_shapes, **side_inputs):
1037     """Predicts the output tensors from second stage of Faster R-CNN.
1038 
1039     Args:
1040       rpn_features_to_crop: A 4-D float32 or bfloat16 tensor with shape
1041         [batch_size, height, width, depth] representing image features to crop
1042         using the proposal boxes predicted by the RPN.
1043       proposal_boxes_normalized: A float tensor with shape [batch_size,
1044         max_num_proposals, 4] representing the (potentially zero padded)
1045         proposal boxes for all images in the batch.  These boxes are represented
1046         as normalized coordinates.
1047       image_shape: A 1D int32 tensors of size [4] containing the image shape.
1048       true_image_shapes: int32 tensor of shape [batch, 3] where each row is
1049         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
1050         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
1051         with zeros.
1052       **side_inputs: additional tensors that are required by the network.
1053 
1054     Returns:
1055       prediction_dict: a dictionary holding "raw" prediction tensors:
1056         1) refined_box_encodings: a 3-D float32 tensor with shape
1057           [total_num_proposals, num_classes, self._box_coder.code_size]
1058           representing predicted (final) refined box encodings, where
1059           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals. If using a
1060           shared box across classes the shape will instead be
1061           [total_num_proposals, 1, self._box_coder.code_size].
1062         2) class_predictions_with_background: a 3-D float32 tensor with shape
1063           [total_num_proposals, num_classes + 1] containing class
1064           predictions (logits) for each of the anchors, where
1065           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals.
1066           Note that this tensor *includes* background class predictions
1067           (at class index 0).
1068         3) proposal_boxes: A float32 tensor of shape
1069           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing
1070           decoded proposal bounding boxes in absolute coordinates.
1071         4) proposal_boxes_normalized: A float32 tensor of shape
1072           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing decoded proposal
1073           bounding boxes in normalized coordinates. Can be used to override the
1074           boxes proposed by the RPN, thus enabling one to extract features and
1075           get box classification and prediction for externally selected areas
1076           of the image.
1077         5) box_classifier_features: a 4-D float32/bfloat16 tensor
1078           representing the features for each proposal.
1079         If self._return_raw_detections_during_predict is True, the dictionary
1080         will also contain:
1081         6) raw_detection_boxes: a 4-D float32 tensor with shape
1082           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, num_classes, 4] in normalized
1083           coordinates.
1084         7) raw_detection_feature_map_indices: a 3-D int32 tensor with shape
1085           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, num_classes].
1086         8) final_anchors: a 3-D float tensor of shape [batch_size,
1087           self.max_num_proposals, 4] containing the reference anchors for raw
1088           detection boxes in normalized coordinates.
1089     """
1090     flattened_proposal_feature_maps = (
1091         self._compute_second_stage_input_feature_maps(
1092             rpn_features_to_crop, proposal_boxes_normalized, **side_inputs))
1093 
1094     box_classifier_features = self._extract_box_classifier_features(
1095         flattened_proposal_feature_maps)
1096 
1097     if self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
1098       box_predictions = self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor(
1099           [box_classifier_features],
1100           prediction_stage=2)
1101     else:
1102       box_predictions = self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.predict(
1103           [box_classifier_features],
1104           num_predictions_per_location=[1],
1105           scope=self.second_stage_box_predictor_scope,
1106           prediction_stage=2)
1107 
1108     refined_box_encodings = tf.squeeze(
1109         box_predictions[box_predictor.BOX_ENCODINGS],
1110         axis=1, name='all_refined_box_encodings')
1111     class_predictions_with_background = tf.squeeze(
1112         box_predictions[box_predictor.CLASS_PREDICTIONS_WITH_BACKGROUND],
1113         axis=1, name='all_class_predictions_with_background')
1114 
1115     absolute_proposal_boxes = ops.normalized_to_image_coordinates(
1116         proposal_boxes_normalized, image_shape, self._parallel_iterations)
1117 
1118     prediction_dict = {
1119         'refined_box_encodings': tf.cast(refined_box_encodings,
1120                                          dtype=tf.float32),
1121         'class_predictions_with_background':
1122         tf.cast(class_predictions_with_background, dtype=tf.float32),
1123         'proposal_boxes': absolute_proposal_boxes,
1124         'box_classifier_features': box_classifier_features,
1125         'proposal_boxes_normalized': proposal_boxes_normalized,
1126         'final_anchors': proposal_boxes_normalized
1127     }
1128 
1129     if self._return_raw_detections_during_predict:
1130       prediction_dict.update(self._raw_detections_and_feature_map_inds(
1131           refined_box_encodings, absolute_proposal_boxes, true_image_shapes))
1132 
1133     return prediction_dict
1134 
1135   def _raw_detections_and_feature_map_inds(
1136       self, refined_box_encodings, absolute_proposal_boxes, true_image_shapes):
1137     """Returns raw detections and feat map inds from where they originated.
1138 
1139     Args:
1140       refined_box_encodings: [total_num_proposals, num_classes,
1141         self._box_coder.code_size] float32 tensor.
1142       absolute_proposal_boxes: [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] float32
1143         tensor representing decoded proposal bounding boxes in absolute
1144         coordinates.
1145       true_image_shapes: [batch, 3] int32 tensor where each row is
1146         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
1147         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
1148         with zeros.
1149 
1150     Returns:
1151       A dictionary with raw detection boxes, and the feature map indices from
1152       which they originated.
1153     """
1154     box_encodings_batch = tf.reshape(
1155         refined_box_encodings,
1156         [-1, self.max_num_proposals, refined_box_encodings.shape[1],
1157          self._box_coder.code_size])
1158     raw_detection_boxes_absolute = self._batch_decode_boxes(
1159         box_encodings_batch, absolute_proposal_boxes)
1160 
1161     raw_detection_boxes_normalized = shape_utils.static_or_dynamic_map_fn(
1162         self._normalize_and_clip_boxes,
1163         elems=[raw_detection_boxes_absolute, true_image_shapes],
1164         dtype=tf.float32)
1165     detection_feature_map_indices = tf.zeros_like(
1166         raw_detection_boxes_normalized[:, :, :, 0], dtype=tf.int32)
1167     return {
1168         fields.PredictionFields.raw_detection_boxes:
1169             raw_detection_boxes_normalized,
1170         fields.PredictionFields.raw_detection_feature_map_indices:
1171             detection_feature_map_indices
1172     }

1174   def _extract_box_classifier_features(self, flattened_feature_maps):
1175     if self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features == (
1176         _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR):
1177       self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features = (
1178           self._feature_extractor.get_box_classifier_feature_extractor_model(
1179               name=self.second_stage_feature_extractor_scope))
1180 
1181     if self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features:
1182       box_classifier_features = (
1183           self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features(
1184               flattened_feature_maps))
1185     else:
1186       box_classifier_features = (
1187           self._feature_extractor.extract_box_classifier_features(
1188               flattened_feature_maps,
1189               scope=self.second_stage_feature_extractor_scope))
1190     return box_classifier_features

1192   def _predict_third_stage(self, prediction_dict, image_shapes):
1193     """Predicts non-box, non-class outputs using refined detections.
1194 
1195     For training, masks as predicted directly on the box_classifier_features,
1196     which are region-features from the initial anchor boxes.
1197     For inference, this happens after calling the post-processing stage, such
1198     that masks are only calculated for the top scored boxes.
1199 
1200     Args:
1201      prediction_dict: a dictionary holding "raw" prediction tensors:
1202         1) refined_box_encodings: a 3-D tensor with shape
1203           [total_num_proposals, num_classes, self._box_coder.code_size]
1204           representing predicted (final) refined box encodings, where
1205           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals. If using a
1206           shared box across classes the shape will instead be
1207           [total_num_proposals, 1, self._box_coder.code_size].
1208         2) class_predictions_with_background: a 3-D tensor with shape
1209           [total_num_proposals, num_classes + 1] containing class
1210           predictions (logits) for each of the anchors, where
1211           total_num_proposals=batch_size*self._max_num_proposals.
1212           Note that this tensor *includes* background class predictions
1213           (at class index 0).
1214         3) num_proposals: An int32 tensor of shape [batch_size] representing the
1215           number of proposals generated by the RPN.  `num_proposals` allows us
1216           to keep track of which entries are to be treated as zero paddings and
1217           which are not since we always pad the number of proposals to be
1218           `self.max_num_proposals` for each image.
1219         4) proposal_boxes: A float32 tensor of shape
1220           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing
1221           decoded proposal bounding boxes in absolute coordinates.
1222         5) box_classifier_features: a 4-D float32 tensor representing the
1223           features for each proposal.
1224       image_shapes: A 2-D int32 tensors of shape [batch_size, 3] containing
1225         shapes of images in the batch.
1226 
1227     Returns:
1228       prediction_dict: a dictionary that in addition to the input predictions
1229       does hold the following predictions as well:
1230         1) mask_predictions: a 4-D tensor with shape
1231           [batch_size, max_detection, mask_height, mask_width] containing
1232           instance mask predictions.
1233     """
1234     if self._is_training:
1235       curr_box_classifier_features = prediction_dict['box_classifier_features']
1236       detection_classes = prediction_dict['class_predictions_with_background']
1237       if self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
1238         mask_predictions = self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor(
1239             [curr_box_classifier_features],
1240             prediction_stage=3)
1241       else:
1242         mask_predictions = self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.predict(
1243             [curr_box_classifier_features],
1244             num_predictions_per_location=[1],
1245             scope=self.second_stage_box_predictor_scope,
1246             prediction_stage=3)
1247       prediction_dict['mask_predictions'] = tf.squeeze(mask_predictions[
1248           box_predictor.MASK_PREDICTIONS], axis=1)
1249     else:
1250       detections_dict = self._postprocess_box_classifier(
1251           prediction_dict['refined_box_encodings'],
1252           prediction_dict['class_predictions_with_background'],
1253           prediction_dict['proposal_boxes'],
1254           prediction_dict['num_proposals'],
1255           image_shapes)
1256       prediction_dict.update(detections_dict)
1257       detection_boxes = detections_dict[
1258           fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_boxes]
1259       detection_classes = detections_dict[
1260           fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_classes]
1261       rpn_features_to_crop = prediction_dict['rpn_features_to_crop']
1262       batch_size = tf.shape(detection_boxes)[0]
1263       max_detection = tf.shape(detection_boxes)[1]
1264       flattened_detected_feature_maps = (
1265           self._compute_second_stage_input_feature_maps(
1266               rpn_features_to_crop, detection_boxes))
1267       curr_box_classifier_features = self._extract_box_classifier_features(
1268           flattened_detected_feature_maps)
1269 
1270       if self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
1271         mask_predictions = self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor(
1272             [curr_box_classifier_features],
1273             prediction_stage=3)
1274       else:
1275         mask_predictions = self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.predict(
1276             [curr_box_classifier_features],
1277             num_predictions_per_location=[1],
1278             scope=self.second_stage_box_predictor_scope,
1279             prediction_stage=3)
1280 
1281       detection_masks = tf.squeeze(mask_predictions[
1282           box_predictor.MASK_PREDICTIONS], axis=1)
1283 
1284       _, num_classes, mask_height, mask_width = (
1285           detection_masks.get_shape().as_list())
1286       _, max_detection = detection_classes.get_shape().as_list()
1287       prediction_dict['mask_predictions'] = tf.reshape(
1288           detection_masks, [-1, num_classes, mask_height, mask_width])
1289       if num_classes > 1:
1290         detection_masks = self._gather_instance_masks(
1291             detection_masks, detection_classes)
1292 
1293       detection_masks = tf.cast(detection_masks, tf.float32)
1294       prediction_dict[fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_masks] = (
1295           tf.reshape(tf.sigmoid(detection_masks),
1296                      [batch_size, max_detection, mask_height, mask_width]))
1297 
1298     return prediction_dict
1299 
1300   def _gather_instance_masks(self, instance_masks, classes):
1301     """Gathers the masks that correspond to classes.
1302 
1303     Args:
1304       instance_masks: A 4-D float32 tensor with shape
1305         [K, num_classes, mask_height, mask_width].
1306       classes: A 2-D int32 tensor with shape [batch_size, max_detection].
1307 
1308     Returns:
1309       masks: a 3-D float32 tensor with shape [K, mask_height, mask_width].
1310     """
1311     _, num_classes, height, width = instance_masks.get_shape().as_list()
1312     k = tf.shape(instance_masks)[0]
1313     instance_masks = tf.reshape(instance_masks, [-1, height, width])
1314     classes = tf.cast(tf.reshape(classes, [-1]), dtype=tf.int32)
1315     gather_idx = tf.range(k) * num_classes + classes
1316     return tf.gather(instance_masks, gather_idx)
1317 
1318   def _extract_rpn_feature_maps(self, preprocessed_inputs):
1319     """Extracts RPN features.
1320 
1321     This function extracts two feature maps: a feature map to be directly
1322     fed to a box predictor (to predict location and objectness scores for
1323     proposals) and a feature map from which to crop regions which will then
1324     be sent to the second stage box classifier.
1325 
1326     Args:
1327       preprocessed_inputs: a [batch, height, width, channels] image tensor.
1328 
1329     Returns:
1330       rpn_box_predictor_features: A 4-D float32 tensor with shape
1331         [batch, height, width, depth] to be used for predicting proposal boxes
1332         and corresponding objectness scores.
1333       rpn_features_to_crop: A 4-D float32 tensor with shape
1334         [batch, height, width, depth] representing image features to crop using
1335         the proposals boxes.
1336       anchors: A BoxList representing anchors (for the RPN) in
1337         absolute coordinates.
1338       image_shape: A 1-D tensor representing the input image shape.
1339     """
1340     image_shape = tf.shape(preprocessed_inputs)
1341 
1342     rpn_features_to_crop, self.endpoints = self._extract_proposal_features(
1343         preprocessed_inputs)
1344 
1345     feature_map_shape = tf.shape(rpn_features_to_crop)
1346     anchors = box_list_ops.concatenate(
1347         self._first_stage_anchor_generator.generate([(feature_map_shape[1],
1348                                                       feature_map_shape[2])]))
1349     rpn_box_predictor_features = (
1350         self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv(rpn_features_to_crop))
1351     return (rpn_box_predictor_features, rpn_features_to_crop,
1352             anchors, image_shape)
1353 
1354   def _extract_proposal_features(self, preprocessed_inputs):

1356         _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR):
1357       self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features = (
1358           self._feature_extractor.get_proposal_feature_extractor_model(
1359               name=self.first_stage_feature_extractor_scope))
1360     if self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features:
1361       proposal_features = (
1362           self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features(preprocessed_inputs),
1363           {})
1364     else:
1365       proposal_features = (
1366           self._feature_extractor.extract_proposal_features(
1367               preprocessed_inputs,
1368               scope=self.first_stage_feature_extractor_scope))
1369     return proposal_features

1371   def _predict_rpn_proposals(self, rpn_box_predictor_features):
1372     """Adds box predictors to RPN feature map to predict proposals.
1373 
1374     Note resulting tensors will not have been postprocessed.
1375 
1376     Args:
1377       rpn_box_predictor_features: A 4-D float32 tensor with shape
1378         [batch, height, width, depth] to be used for predicting proposal boxes
1379         and corresponding objectness scores.
1380 
1381     Returns:
1382       box_encodings: 3-D float tensor of shape
1383         [batch_size, num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
1384         predicted boxes.
1385       objectness_predictions_with_background: 3-D float tensor of shape
1386         [batch_size, num_anchors, 2] containing class
1387         predictions (logits) for each of the anchors.  Note that this
1388         tensor *includes* background class predictions (at class index 0).
1389 
1390     Raises:
1391       RuntimeError: if the anchor generator generates anchors corresponding to
1392         multiple feature maps.  We currently assume that a single feature map
1393         is generated for the RPN.
1394     """
1395     num_anchors_per_location = (
1396         self._first_stage_anchor_generator.num_anchors_per_location())
1397     if len(num_anchors_per_location) != 1:
1398       raise RuntimeError('anchor_generator is expected to generate anchors '
1399                          'corresponding to a single feature map.')
1400     if self._first_stage_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
1401       box_predictions = self._first_stage_box_predictor(
1402           [rpn_box_predictor_features])
1403     else:
1404       box_predictions = self._first_stage_box_predictor.predict(
1405           [rpn_box_predictor_features],
1406           num_anchors_per_location,
1407           scope=self.first_stage_box_predictor_scope)
1408 
1409     box_encodings = tf.concat(
1410         box_predictions[box_predictor.BOX_ENCODINGS], axis=1)
1411     objectness_predictions_with_background = tf.concat(
1412         box_predictions[box_predictor.CLASS_PREDICTIONS_WITH_BACKGROUND],
1413         axis=1)
1414     return (tf.squeeze(box_encodings, axis=2),
1415             objectness_predictions_with_background)
1416 
1417   def _remove_invalid_anchors_and_predictions(
1418       self,
1419       box_encodings,
1420       objectness_predictions_with_background,
1421       anchors_boxlist,
1422       clip_window):
1423     """Removes anchors that (partially) fall outside an image.
1424 
1425     Also removes associated box encodings and objectness predictions.
1426 
1427     Args:
1428       box_encodings: 3-D float tensor of shape
1429         [batch_size, num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
1430         predicted boxes.
1431       objectness_predictions_with_background: 3-D float tensor of shape
1432         [batch_size, num_anchors, 2] containing class
1433         predictions (logits) for each of the anchors.  Note that this
1434         tensor *includes* background class predictions (at class index 0).
1435       anchors_boxlist: A BoxList representing num_anchors anchors (for the RPN)
1436         in absolute coordinates.
1437       clip_window: a 1-D tensor representing the [ymin, xmin, ymax, xmax]
1438         extent of the window to clip/prune to.
1439 
1440     Returns:
1441       box_encodings: 4-D float tensor of shape
1442         [batch_size, num_valid_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
1443         predicted boxes, where num_valid_anchors <= num_anchors
1444       objectness_predictions_with_background: 2-D float tensor of shape
1445         [batch_size, num_valid_anchors, 2] containing class
1446         predictions (logits) for each of the anchors, where
1447         num_valid_anchors <= num_anchors.  Note that this
1448         tensor *includes* background class predictions (at class index 0).
1449       anchors: A BoxList representing num_valid_anchors anchors (for the RPN) in
1450         absolute coordinates.
1451     """
1452     pruned_anchors_boxlist, keep_indices = box_list_ops.prune_outside_window(
1453         anchors_boxlist, clip_window)
1454     def _batch_gather_kept_indices(predictions_tensor):
1455       return shape_utils.static_or_dynamic_map_fn(
1456           functools.partial(tf.gather, indices=keep_indices),
1457           elems=predictions_tensor,
1458           dtype=tf.float32,
1459           parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations,
1460           back_prop=True)
1461     return (_batch_gather_kept_indices(box_encodings),
1462             _batch_gather_kept_indices(objectness_predictions_with_background),
1463             pruned_anchors_boxlist)
1464 
1465   def _flatten_first_two_dimensions(self, inputs):
1466     """Flattens `K-d` tensor along batch dimension to be a `(K-1)-d` tensor.
1467 
1468     Converts `inputs` with shape [A, B, ..., depth] into a tensor of shape
1469     [A * B, ..., depth].
1470 
1471     Args:
1472       inputs: A float tensor with shape [A, B, ..., depth].  Note that the first
1473         two and last dimensions must be statically defined.
1474     Returns:
1475       A float tensor with shape [A * B, ..., depth] (where the first and last
1476         dimension are statically defined.
1477     """
1478     combined_shape = shape_utils.combined_static_and_dynamic_shape(inputs)
1479     flattened_shape = tf.stack([combined_shape[0] * combined_shape[1]] +
1480                                combined_shape[2:])
1481     return tf.reshape(inputs, flattened_shape)
1482 
1483   def postprocess(self, prediction_dict, true_image_shapes):
1484     """Convert prediction tensors to final detections.
1485 
1486     This function converts raw predictions tensors to final detection results.
1487     See base class for output format conventions.  Note also that by default,
1488     scores are to be interpreted as logits, but if a score_converter is used,
1489     then scores are remapped (and may thus have a different interpretation).
1490 
1491     If number_of_stages=1, the returned results represent proposals from the
1492     first stage RPN and are padded to have self.max_num_proposals for each
1493     image; otherwise, the results can be interpreted as multiclass detections
1494     from the full two-stage model and are padded to self._max_detections.
1495 
1496     Args:
1497       prediction_dict: a dictionary holding prediction tensors (see the
1498         documentation for the predict method.  If number_of_stages=1, we
1499         expect prediction_dict to contain `rpn_box_encodings`,
1500         `rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background`, `rpn_features_to_crop`,
1501         and `anchors` fields.  Otherwise we expect prediction_dict to
1502         additionally contain `refined_box_encodings`,
1503         `class_predictions_with_background`, `num_proposals`,
1504         `proposal_boxes` and, optionally, `mask_predictions` fields.
1505       true_image_shapes: int32 tensor of shape [batch, 3] where each row is
1506         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
1507         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
1508         with zeros.
1509 
1510     Returns:
1511       detections: a dictionary containing the following fields
1512         detection_boxes: [batch, max_detection, 4]
1513         detection_scores: [batch, max_detections]
1514         detection_multiclass_scores: [batch, max_detections, 2]
1515         detection_anchor_indices: [batch, max_detections]
1516         detection_classes: [batch, max_detections]
1517           (this entry is only created if rpn_mode=False)
1518         num_detections: [batch]
1519         raw_detection_boxes: [batch, total_detections, 4]
1520         raw_detection_scores: [batch, total_detections, num_classes + 1]
1521 
1522     Raises:
1523       ValueError: If `predict` is called before `preprocess`.
1524       ValueError: If `_output_final_box_features` is true but
1525         rpn_features_to_crop is not in the prediction_dict.
1526     """
1527 
1528     with tf.name_scope('FirstStagePostprocessor'):
1529       if self._number_of_stages == 1:
1530 
1531         image_shapes = self._image_batch_shape_2d(
1532             prediction_dict['image_shape'])
1533         (proposal_boxes, proposal_scores, proposal_multiclass_scores,
1534          num_proposals, raw_proposal_boxes,
1535          raw_proposal_scores) = self._postprocess_rpn(
1536              prediction_dict['rpn_box_encodings'],
1537              prediction_dict['rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background'],
1538              prediction_dict['anchors'], image_shapes, true_image_shapes)
1539         return {
1540             fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_boxes:
1541                 proposal_boxes,
1542             fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_scores:
1543                 proposal_scores,
1544             fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_multiclass_scores:
1545                 proposal_multiclass_scores,
1546             fields.DetectionResultFields.num_detections:
1547                 tf.cast(num_proposals, dtype=tf.float32),
1548             fields.DetectionResultFields.raw_detection_boxes:
1549                 raw_proposal_boxes,
1550             fields.DetectionResultFields.raw_detection_scores:
1551                 raw_proposal_scores
1552         }
1553 
1554     # TODO(jrru): Remove mask_predictions from _post_process_box_classifier.
1555     if (self._number_of_stages == 2 or
1556         (self._number_of_stages == 3 and self._is_training)):
1557       with tf.name_scope('SecondStagePostprocessor'):
1558         mask_predictions = prediction_dict.get(box_predictor.MASK_PREDICTIONS)
1559         detections_dict = self._postprocess_box_classifier(
1560             prediction_dict['refined_box_encodings'],
1561             prediction_dict['class_predictions_with_background'],
1562             prediction_dict['proposal_boxes'],
1563             prediction_dict['num_proposals'],
