1564             true_image_shapes,
1565             mask_predictions=mask_predictions)
1566 
1567       if self._output_final_box_features:
1568         if 'rpn_features_to_crop' not in prediction_dict:
1569           raise ValueError(
1570               'Please make sure rpn_features_to_crop is in the prediction_dict.'
1571           )
1572         detections_dict[
1573             'detection_features'] = self._add_detection_features_output_node(
1574                 detections_dict[fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_boxes],
1575                 prediction_dict['rpn_features_to_crop'])
1576 
1577       return detections_dict
1578 
1579     if self._number_of_stages == 3:
1580       # Post processing is already performed in 3rd stage. We need to transfer
1581       # postprocessed tensors from `prediction_dict` to `detections_dict`.
1582       # Remove any items from the prediction dictionary if they are not pure
1583       # Tensors.
1584       non_tensor_predictions = [
1585           k for k, v in prediction_dict.items() if not isinstance(v, tf.Tensor)]
1586       for k in non_tensor_predictions:
1587         tf.logging.info('Removing {0} from prediction_dict'.format(k))
1588         prediction_dict.pop(k)
1589       return prediction_dict
1590 
1591   def _add_detection_features_output_node(self, detection_boxes,
1592                                           rpn_features_to_crop):
1593     """Add detection features to outputs.
1594 
1595     This function extracts box features for each box in rpn_features_to_crop.
1596     It returns the extracted box features, reshaped to
1597     [batch size, max_detections, height, width, depth], and average pools
1598     the extracted features across the spatial dimensions and adds a graph node
1599     to the pooled features named 'pooled_detection_features'
1600 
1601     Args:
1602       detection_boxes: a 3-D float32 tensor of shape
1603         [batch_size, max_detections, 4] which represents the bounding boxes.
1604       rpn_features_to_crop: A 4-D float32 tensor with shape
1605         [batch, height, width, depth] representing image features to crop using
1606         the proposals boxes.
1607 
1608     Returns:
1609       detection_features: a 4-D float32 tensor of shape
1610         [batch size, max_detections, height, width, depth] representing
1611         cropped image features
1612     """
1613     with tf.name_scope('SecondStageDetectionFeaturesExtract'):
1614       flattened_detected_feature_maps = (
1615           self._compute_second_stage_input_feature_maps(
1616               rpn_features_to_crop, detection_boxes))
1617       detection_features_unpooled = self._extract_box_classifier_features(
1618           flattened_detected_feature_maps)
1619 
1620       batch_size = tf.shape(detection_boxes)[0]
1621       max_detections = tf.shape(detection_boxes)[1]
1622       detection_features_pool = tf.reduce_mean(
1623           detection_features_unpooled, axis=[1, 2])
1624       reshaped_detection_features_pool = tf.reshape(
1625           detection_features_pool,
1626           [batch_size, max_detections, tf.shape(detection_features_pool)[-1]])
1627       reshaped_detection_features_pool = tf.identity(
1628           reshaped_detection_features_pool, 'pooled_detection_features')
1629 
1630       reshaped_detection_features = tf.reshape(
1631           detection_features_unpooled,
1632           [batch_size, max_detections,
1633            tf.shape(detection_features_unpooled)[1],
1634            tf.shape(detection_features_unpooled)[2],
1635            tf.shape(detection_features_unpooled)[3]])
1636 
1637     return reshaped_detection_features
1638 
1639   def _postprocess_rpn(self,
1640                        rpn_box_encodings_batch,
1641                        rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background_batch,
1642                        anchors,
1643                        image_shapes,
1644                        true_image_shapes):
1645     """Converts first stage prediction tensors from the RPN to proposals.
1646 
1647     This function decodes the raw RPN predictions, runs non-max suppression
1648     on the result.
1649 
1650     Note that the behavior of this function is slightly modified during
1651     training --- specifically, we stop the gradient from passing through the
1652     proposal boxes and we only return a balanced sampled subset of proposals
1653     with size `second_stage_batch_size`.
1654 
1655     Args:
1656       rpn_box_encodings_batch: A 3-D float32 tensor of shape
1657         [batch_size, num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
1658         predicted proposal box encodings.
1659       rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background_batch: A 3-D float tensor of
1660         shape [batch_size, num_anchors, 2] containing objectness predictions
1661         (logits) for each of the anchors with 0 corresponding to background
1662         and 1 corresponding to object.
1663       anchors: A 2-D tensor of shape [num_anchors, 4] representing anchors
1664         for the first stage RPN.  Note that `num_anchors` can differ depending
1665         on whether the model is created in training or inference mode.
1666       image_shapes: A 2-D tensor of shape [batch, 3] containing the shapes of
1667         images in the batch.
1668       true_image_shapes: int32 tensor of shape [batch, 3] where each row is
1669         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
1670         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
1671         with zeros.
1672 
1673     Returns:
1674       proposal_boxes: A float tensor with shape
1675         [batch_size, max_num_proposals, 4] representing the (potentially zero
1676         padded) proposal boxes for all images in the batch.  These boxes are
1677         represented as normalized coordinates.
1678       proposal_scores:  A float tensor with shape
1679         [batch_size, max_num_proposals] representing the (potentially zero
1680         padded) proposal objectness scores for all images in the batch.
1681       proposal_multiclass_scores:  A float tensor with shape
1682         [batch_size, max_num_proposals, 2] representing the (potentially zero
1683         padded) proposal multiclass scores for all images in the batch.
1684       num_proposals: A Tensor of type `int32`. A 1-D tensor of shape [batch]
1685         representing the number of proposals predicted for each image in
1686         the batch.
1687       raw_detection_boxes: [batch, total_detections, 4] tensor with decoded
1688         proposal boxes before Non-Max Suppression.
1689       raw_detection_scores: [batch, total_detections,
1690         num_classes_with_background] tensor of multi-class scores for raw
1691         proposal boxes.
1692     """
1693     rpn_box_encodings_batch = tf.expand_dims(rpn_box_encodings_batch, axis=2)
1694     rpn_encodings_shape = shape_utils.combined_static_and_dynamic_shape(
1695         rpn_box_encodings_batch)
1696     tiled_anchor_boxes = tf.tile(
1697         tf.expand_dims(anchors, 0), [rpn_encodings_shape[0], 1, 1])
1698     proposal_boxes = self._batch_decode_boxes(rpn_box_encodings_batch,
1699                                               tiled_anchor_boxes)
1700     raw_proposal_boxes = tf.squeeze(proposal_boxes, axis=2)
1701     rpn_objectness_softmax = tf.nn.softmax(
1702         rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background_batch)
1703     rpn_objectness_softmax_without_background = rpn_objectness_softmax[:, :, 1]
1704     clip_window = self._compute_clip_window(true_image_shapes)
1705     additional_fields = {'multiclass_scores': rpn_objectness_softmax}
1706     (proposal_boxes, proposal_scores, _, _, nmsed_additional_fields,
1707      num_proposals) = self._first_stage_nms_fn(
1708          tf.expand_dims(raw_proposal_boxes, axis=2),
1709          tf.expand_dims(rpn_objectness_softmax_without_background, axis=2),
1710          additional_fields=additional_fields,
1711          clip_window=clip_window)
1712     if self._is_training:
1713       proposal_boxes = tf.stop_gradient(proposal_boxes)
1714       if not self._hard_example_miner:
1715         (groundtruth_boxlists, groundtruth_classes_with_background_list, _,
1716          groundtruth_weights_list
1717         ) = self._format_groundtruth_data(image_shapes)
1718         (proposal_boxes, proposal_scores,
1719          num_proposals) = self._sample_box_classifier_batch(
1720              proposal_boxes, proposal_scores, num_proposals,
1721              groundtruth_boxlists, groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
1722              groundtruth_weights_list)
1723     # normalize proposal boxes
1724     def normalize_boxes(args):
1725       proposal_boxes_per_image = args[0]
1726       image_shape = args[1]
1727       normalized_boxes_per_image = box_list_ops.to_normalized_coordinates(
1728           box_list.BoxList(proposal_boxes_per_image), image_shape[0],
1729           image_shape[1], check_range=False).get()
1730       return normalized_boxes_per_image
1731     normalized_proposal_boxes = shape_utils.static_or_dynamic_map_fn(
1732         normalize_boxes, elems=[proposal_boxes, image_shapes], dtype=tf.float32)
1733     raw_normalized_proposal_boxes = shape_utils.static_or_dynamic_map_fn(
1734         normalize_boxes,
1735         elems=[raw_proposal_boxes, image_shapes],
1736         dtype=tf.float32)
1737     proposal_multiclass_scores = (
1738         nmsed_additional_fields.get('multiclass_scores')
1739         if nmsed_additional_fields else None)
1740     return (normalized_proposal_boxes, proposal_scores,
1741             proposal_multiclass_scores, num_proposals,
1742             raw_normalized_proposal_boxes, rpn_objectness_softmax)
1743 
1744   def _sample_box_classifier_batch(
1745       self,
1746       proposal_boxes,
1747       proposal_scores,
1748       num_proposals,
1749       groundtruth_boxlists,
1750       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
1751       groundtruth_weights_list):
1752     """Samples a minibatch for second stage.
1753 
1754     Args:
1755       proposal_boxes: A float tensor with shape
1756         [batch_size, num_proposals, 4] representing the (potentially zero
1757         padded) proposal boxes for all images in the batch.  These boxes are
1758         represented in absolute coordinates.
1759       proposal_scores:  A float tensor with shape
1760         [batch_size, num_proposals] representing the (potentially zero
1761         padded) proposal objectness scores for all images in the batch.
1762       num_proposals: A Tensor of type `int32`. A 1-D tensor of shape [batch]
1763         representing the number of proposals predicted for each image in
1764         the batch.
1765       groundtruth_boxlists: A list of BoxLists containing (absolute) coordinates
1766         of the groundtruth boxes.
1767       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list: A list of 2-D one-hot
1768         (or k-hot) tensors of shape [num_boxes, num_classes+1] containing the
1769         class targets with the 0th index assumed to map to the background class.
1770       groundtruth_weights_list: A list of 1-D tensors of shape [num_boxes]
1771         indicating the weight associated with the groundtruth boxes.
1772 
1773     Returns:
1774       proposal_boxes: A float tensor with shape
1775         [batch_size, second_stage_batch_size, 4] representing the (potentially
1776         zero padded) proposal boxes for all images in the batch.  These boxes
1777         are represented in absolute coordinates.
1778       proposal_scores:  A float tensor with shape
1779         [batch_size, second_stage_batch_size] representing the (potentially zero
1780         padded) proposal objectness scores for all images in the batch.
1781       num_proposals: A Tensor of type `int32`. A 1-D tensor of shape [batch]
1782         representing the number of proposals predicted for each image in
1783         the batch.
1784     """
1785     single_image_proposal_box_sample = []
1786     single_image_proposal_score_sample = []
1787     single_image_num_proposals_sample = []
1788     for (single_image_proposal_boxes,
1789          single_image_proposal_scores,
1790          single_image_num_proposals,
1791          single_image_groundtruth_boxlist,
1792          single_image_groundtruth_classes_with_background,
1793          single_image_groundtruth_weights) in zip(
1794              tf.unstack(proposal_boxes),
1795              tf.unstack(proposal_scores),
1796              tf.unstack(num_proposals),
1797              groundtruth_boxlists,
1798              groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
1799              groundtruth_weights_list):
1800       single_image_boxlist = box_list.BoxList(single_image_proposal_boxes)
1801       single_image_boxlist.add_field(fields.BoxListFields.scores,
1802                                      single_image_proposal_scores)
1803       sampled_boxlist = self._sample_box_classifier_minibatch_single_image(
1804           single_image_boxlist,
1805           single_image_num_proposals,
1806           single_image_groundtruth_boxlist,
1807           single_image_groundtruth_classes_with_background,
1808           single_image_groundtruth_weights)
1809       sampled_padded_boxlist = box_list_ops.pad_or_clip_box_list(
1810           sampled_boxlist,
1811           num_boxes=self._second_stage_batch_size)
1812       single_image_num_proposals_sample.append(tf.minimum(
1813           sampled_boxlist.num_boxes(),
1814           self._second_stage_batch_size))
1815       bb = sampled_padded_boxlist.get()
1816       single_image_proposal_box_sample.append(bb)
1817       single_image_proposal_score_sample.append(
1818           sampled_padded_boxlist.get_field(fields.BoxListFields.scores))
1819     return (tf.stack(single_image_proposal_box_sample),
1820             tf.stack(single_image_proposal_score_sample),
1821             tf.stack(single_image_num_proposals_sample))
1822 
1823   def _format_groundtruth_data(self, image_shapes):
1824     """Helper function for preparing groundtruth data for target assignment.
1825 
1826     In order to be consistent with the model.DetectionModel interface,
1827     groundtruth boxes are specified in normalized coordinates and classes are
1828     specified as label indices with no assumed background category.  To prepare
1829     for target assignment, we:
1830     1) convert boxes to absolute coordinates,
1831     2) add a background class at class index 0
1832     3) groundtruth instance masks, if available, are resized to match
1833        image_shape.
1834 
1835     Args:
1836       image_shapes: a 2-D int32 tensor of shape [batch_size, 3] containing
1837         shapes of input image in the batch.
1838 
1839     Returns:
1840       groundtruth_boxlists: A list of BoxLists containing (absolute) coordinates
1841         of the groundtruth boxes.
1842       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list: A list of 2-D one-hot
1843         (or k-hot) tensors of shape [num_boxes, num_classes+1] containing the
1844         class targets with the 0th index assumed to map to the background class.
1845       groundtruth_masks_list: If present, a list of 3-D tf.float32 tensors of
1846         shape [num_boxes, image_height, image_width] containing instance masks.
1847         This is set to None if no masks exist in the provided groundtruth.
1848     """
1849     # pylint: disable=g-complex-comprehension
1850     groundtruth_boxlists = [
1851         box_list_ops.to_absolute_coordinates(
1852             box_list.BoxList(boxes), image_shapes[i, 0], image_shapes[i, 1])
1853         for i, boxes in enumerate(
1854             self.groundtruth_lists(fields.BoxListFields.boxes))
1855     ]
1856     groundtruth_classes_with_background_list = []
1857     for one_hot_encoding in self.groundtruth_lists(
1858         fields.BoxListFields.classes):
1859       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list.append(
1860           tf.cast(
1861               tf.pad(one_hot_encoding, [[0, 0], [1, 0]], mode='CONSTANT'),
1862               dtype=tf.float32))
1863 
1864     groundtruth_masks_list = self._groundtruth_lists.get(
1865         fields.BoxListFields.masks)
1866     # TODO(rathodv): Remove mask resizing once the legacy pipeline is deleted.
1867     if groundtruth_masks_list is not None and self._resize_masks:
1868       resized_masks_list = []
1869       for mask in groundtruth_masks_list:
1870 
1871         _, resized_mask, _ = self._image_resizer_fn(
1872             # Reuse the given `image_resizer_fn` to resize groundtruth masks.
1873             # `mask` tensor for an image is of the shape [num_masks,
1874             # image_height, image_width]. Below we create a dummy image of the
1875             # the shape [image_height, image_width, 1] to use with
1876             # `image_resizer_fn`.
1877             image=tf.zeros(tf.stack([tf.shape(mask)[1],
1878                                      tf.shape(mask)[2], 1])),
1879             masks=mask)
1880         resized_masks_list.append(resized_mask)
1881 
1882       groundtruth_masks_list = resized_masks_list
1883     # Masks could be set to bfloat16 in the input pipeline for performance
1884     # reasons. Convert masks back to floating point space here since the rest of
1885     # this module assumes groundtruth to be of float32 type.
1886     float_groundtruth_masks_list = []
1887     if groundtruth_masks_list:
1888       for mask in groundtruth_masks_list:
1889         float_groundtruth_masks_list.append(tf.cast(mask, tf.float32))
1890       groundtruth_masks_list = float_groundtruth_masks_list
1891 
1892     if self.groundtruth_has_field(fields.BoxListFields.weights):
1893       groundtruth_weights_list = self.groundtruth_lists(
1894           fields.BoxListFields.weights)
1895     else:
1896       # Set weights for all batch elements equally to 1.0
1897       groundtruth_weights_list = []
1898       for groundtruth_classes in groundtruth_classes_with_background_list:
1899         num_gt = tf.shape(groundtruth_classes)[0]
1900         groundtruth_weights = tf.ones(num_gt)
1901         groundtruth_weights_list.append(groundtruth_weights)
1902 
1903     return (groundtruth_boxlists, groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
1904             groundtruth_masks_list, groundtruth_weights_list)
1905 
1906   def _sample_box_classifier_minibatch_single_image(
1907       self, proposal_boxlist, num_valid_proposals, groundtruth_boxlist,
1908       groundtruth_classes_with_background, groundtruth_weights):
1909     """Samples a mini-batch of proposals to be sent to the box classifier.
1910 
1911     Helper function for self._postprocess_rpn.
1912 
1913     Args:
1914       proposal_boxlist: A BoxList containing K proposal boxes in absolute
1915         coordinates.
1916       num_valid_proposals: Number of valid proposals in the proposal boxlist.
1917       groundtruth_boxlist: A Boxlist containing N groundtruth object boxes in
1918         absolute coordinates.
1919       groundtruth_classes_with_background: A tensor with shape
1920         `[N, self.num_classes + 1]` representing groundtruth classes. The
1921         classes are assumed to be k-hot encoded, and include background as the
1922         zero-th class.
1923       groundtruth_weights: Weights attached to the groundtruth_boxes.
1924 
1925     Returns:
1926       a BoxList contained sampled proposals.
1927     """
1928     (cls_targets, cls_weights, _, _, _) = self._detector_target_assigner.assign(
1929         proposal_boxlist,
1930         groundtruth_boxlist,
1931         groundtruth_classes_with_background,
1932         unmatched_class_label=tf.constant(
1933             [1] + self._num_classes * [0], dtype=tf.float32),
1934         groundtruth_weights=groundtruth_weights)
1935     # Selects all boxes as candidates if none of them is selected according
1936     # to cls_weights. This could happen as boxes within certain IOU ranges
1937     # are ignored. If triggered, the selected boxes will still be ignored
1938     # during loss computation.
1939     cls_weights = tf.reduce_mean(cls_weights, axis=-1)
1940     positive_indicator = tf.greater(tf.argmax(cls_targets, axis=1), 0)
1941     valid_indicator = tf.logical_and(
1942         tf.range(proposal_boxlist.num_boxes()) < num_valid_proposals,
1943         cls_weights > 0
1944     )
1945     selected_positions = self._second_stage_sampler.subsample(
1946         valid_indicator,
1947         self._second_stage_batch_size,
1948         positive_indicator)
1949     return box_list_ops.boolean_mask(
1950         proposal_boxlist,
1951         selected_positions,
1952         use_static_shapes=self._use_static_shapes,
1953         indicator_sum=(self._second_stage_batch_size
1954                        if self._use_static_shapes else None))
1955 
1956   def _compute_second_stage_input_feature_maps(self, features_to_crop,
1957                                                proposal_boxes_normalized,
1958                                                **side_inputs):
1959     """Crops to a set of proposals from the feature map for a batch of images.
1960 
1961     Helper function for self._postprocess_rpn. This function calls
1962     `tf.image.crop_and_resize` to create the feature map to be passed to the
1963     second stage box classifier for each proposal.
1964 
1965     Args:
1966       features_to_crop: A float32 tensor with shape
1967         [batch_size, height, width, depth]
1968       proposal_boxes_normalized: A float32 tensor with shape [batch_size,
1969         num_proposals, box_code_size] containing proposal boxes in
1970         normalized coordinates.
1971       **side_inputs: additional tensors that are required by the network.
1972 
1973     Returns:
1974       A float32 tensor with shape [K, new_height, new_width, depth].
1975     """
1976     cropped_regions = self._flatten_first_two_dimensions(
1977         self._crop_and_resize_fn(
1978             features_to_crop, proposal_boxes_normalized,
1979             [self._initial_crop_size, self._initial_crop_size]))
1980     return self._maxpool_layer(cropped_regions)
1981 
1982   def _postprocess_box_classifier(self,
1983                                   refined_box_encodings,
1984                                   class_predictions_with_background,
1985                                   proposal_boxes,
1986                                   num_proposals,
1987                                   image_shapes,
1988                                   mask_predictions=None):
1989     """Converts predictions from the second stage box classifier to detections.
1990 
1991     Args:
1992       refined_box_encodings: a 3-D float tensor with shape
1993         [total_num_padded_proposals, num_classes, self._box_coder.code_size]
1994         representing predicted (final) refined box encodings. If using a shared
1995         box across classes the shape will instead be
1996         [total_num_padded_proposals, 1, 4]
1997       class_predictions_with_background: a 2-D tensor float with shape
1998         [total_num_padded_proposals, num_classes + 1] containing class
1999         predictions (logits) for each of the proposals.  Note that this tensor
2000         *includes* background class predictions (at class index 0).
2001       proposal_boxes: a 3-D float tensor with shape
2002         [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing decoded proposal
2003         bounding boxes in absolute coordinates.
2004       num_proposals: a 1-D int32 tensor of shape [batch] representing the number
2005         of proposals predicted for each image in the batch.
2006       image_shapes: a 2-D int32 tensor containing shapes of input image in the
2007         batch.
2008       mask_predictions: (optional) a 4-D float tensor with shape
2009         [total_num_padded_proposals, num_classes, mask_height, mask_width]
2010         containing instance mask prediction logits.
2011 
2012     Returns:
2013       A dictionary containing:
2014         `detection_boxes`: [batch, max_detection, 4] in normalized co-ordinates.
2015         `detection_scores`: [batch, max_detections]
2016          `detection_multiclass_scores`: [batch, max_detections,
2017           num_classes_with_background] tensor with class score distribution for
2018           post-processed detection boxes including background class if any.
2019         `detection_anchor_indices`: [batch, max_detections] with anchor
2020           indices.
2021         `detection_classes`: [batch, max_detections]
2022         `num_detections`: [batch]
2023         `detection_masks`:
2024           (optional) [batch, max_detections, mask_height, mask_width]. Note
2025           that a pixel-wise sigmoid score converter is applied to the detection
2026           masks.
2027         `raw_detection_boxes`: [batch, total_detections, 4] tensor with decoded
2028           detection boxes in normalized coordinates, before Non-Max Suppression.
2029           The value total_detections is the number of second stage anchors
2030           (i.e. the total number of boxes before NMS).
2031         `raw_detection_scores`: [batch, total_detections,
2032           num_classes_with_background] tensor of multi-class scores for
2033           raw detection boxes. The value total_detections is the number of
2034           second stage anchors (i.e. the total number of boxes before NMS).
2035     """
2036     refined_box_encodings_batch = tf.reshape(
2037         refined_box_encodings,
2038         [-1,
2039          self.max_num_proposals,
2040          refined_box_encodings.shape[1],
2041          self._box_coder.code_size])
2042     class_predictions_with_background_batch = tf.reshape(
2043         class_predictions_with_background,
2044         [-1, self.max_num_proposals, self.num_classes + 1]
2045     )
2046     refined_decoded_boxes_batch = self._batch_decode_boxes(
2047         refined_box_encodings_batch, proposal_boxes)
2048     class_predictions_with_background_batch_normalized = (
2049         self._second_stage_score_conversion_fn(
2050             class_predictions_with_background_batch))
2051     class_predictions_batch = tf.reshape(
2052         tf.slice(class_predictions_with_background_batch_normalized,
2053                  [0, 0, 1], [-1, -1, -1]),
2054         [-1, self.max_num_proposals, self.num_classes])
2055     clip_window = self._compute_clip_window(image_shapes)
2056     mask_predictions_batch = None
2057     if mask_predictions is not None:
2058       mask_height = shape_utils.get_dim_as_int(mask_predictions.shape[2])
2059       mask_width = shape_utils.get_dim_as_int(mask_predictions.shape[3])
2060       mask_predictions = tf.sigmoid(mask_predictions)
2061       mask_predictions_batch = tf.reshape(
2062           mask_predictions, [-1, self.max_num_proposals,
2063                              self.num_classes, mask_height, mask_width])
2064 
2065     batch_size = shape_utils.combined_static_and_dynamic_shape(
2066         refined_box_encodings_batch)[0]
2067     batch_anchor_indices = tf.tile(
2068         tf.expand_dims(tf.range(self.max_num_proposals), 0),
2069         multiples=[batch_size, 1])
2070     additional_fields = {
2071         'multiclass_scores': class_predictions_with_background_batch_normalized,
2072         'anchor_indices': tf.cast(batch_anchor_indices, tf.float32)
2073     }
2074     (nmsed_boxes, nmsed_scores, nmsed_classes, nmsed_masks,
2075      nmsed_additional_fields, num_detections) = self._second_stage_nms_fn(
2076          refined_decoded_boxes_batch,
2077          class_predictions_batch,
2078          clip_window=clip_window,
2079          change_coordinate_frame=True,
2080          num_valid_boxes=num_proposals,
2081          additional_fields=additional_fields,
2082          masks=mask_predictions_batch)
2083     if refined_decoded_boxes_batch.shape[2] > 1:
2084       class_ids = tf.expand_dims(
2085           tf.argmax(class_predictions_with_background_batch[:, :, 1:], axis=2,
2086                     output_type=tf.int32),
2087           axis=-1)
2088       raw_detection_boxes = tf.squeeze(
2089           tf.batch_gather(refined_decoded_boxes_batch, class_ids), axis=2)
2090     else:
2091       raw_detection_boxes = tf.squeeze(refined_decoded_boxes_batch, axis=2)
2092 
2093     raw_normalized_detection_boxes = shape_utils.static_or_dynamic_map_fn(
2094         self._normalize_and_clip_boxes,
2095         elems=[raw_detection_boxes, image_shapes],
2096         dtype=tf.float32)
2097 
2098     detections = {
2099         fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_boxes:
2100             nmsed_boxes,
2101         fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_scores:
2102             nmsed_scores,
2103         fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_classes:
2104             nmsed_classes,
2105         fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_multiclass_scores:
2106             nmsed_additional_fields['multiclass_scores'],
2107         fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_anchor_indices:
2108             tf.cast(nmsed_additional_fields['anchor_indices'], tf.int32),
2109         fields.DetectionResultFields.num_detections:
2110             tf.cast(num_detections, dtype=tf.float32),
2111         fields.DetectionResultFields.raw_detection_boxes:
2112             raw_normalized_detection_boxes,
2113         fields.DetectionResultFields.raw_detection_scores:
2114             class_predictions_with_background_batch_normalized
2115     }
2116     if nmsed_masks is not None:
2117       detections[fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_masks] = nmsed_masks
2118     return detections
2119 
2120   def _batch_decode_boxes(self, box_encodings, anchor_boxes):
2121     """Decodes box encodings with respect to the anchor boxes.
2122 
2123     Args:
2124       box_encodings: a 4-D tensor with shape
2125         [batch_size, num_anchors, num_classes, self._box_coder.code_size]
2126         representing box encodings.
2127       anchor_boxes: [batch_size, num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size]
2128         representing decoded bounding boxes. If using a shared box across
2129         classes the shape will instead be
2130         [total_num_proposals, 1, self._box_coder.code_size].
2131 
2132     Returns:
2133       decoded_boxes: a
2134         [batch_size, num_anchors, num_classes, self._box_coder.code_size]
2135         float tensor representing bounding box predictions (for each image in
2136         batch, proposal and class). If using a shared box across classes the
2137         shape will instead be
2138         [batch_size, num_anchors, 1, self._box_coder.code_size].
2139     """
2140     combined_shape = shape_utils.combined_static_and_dynamic_shape(
2141         box_encodings)
2142     num_classes = combined_shape[2]
2143     tiled_anchor_boxes = tf.tile(
2144         tf.expand_dims(anchor_boxes, 2), [1, 1, num_classes, 1])
2145     tiled_anchors_boxlist = box_list.BoxList(
2146         tf.reshape(tiled_anchor_boxes, [-1, 4]))
2147     decoded_boxes = self._box_coder.decode(
2148         tf.reshape(box_encodings, [-1, self._box_coder.code_size]),
2149         tiled_anchors_boxlist)
2150     return tf.reshape(decoded_boxes.get(),
2151                       tf.stack([combined_shape[0], combined_shape[1],
2152                                 num_classes, 4]))
2153 
2154   def _normalize_and_clip_boxes(self, boxes_and_image_shape):
2155     """Normalize and clip boxes."""
2156     boxes_per_image = boxes_and_image_shape[0]
2157     image_shape = boxes_and_image_shape[1]
2158 
2159     boxes_contains_classes_dim = boxes_per_image.shape.ndims == 3
2160     if boxes_contains_classes_dim:
2161       boxes_per_image = shape_utils.flatten_first_n_dimensions(
2162           boxes_per_image, 2)
2163     normalized_boxes_per_image = box_list_ops.to_normalized_coordinates(
2164         box_list.BoxList(boxes_per_image),
2165         image_shape[0],
2166         image_shape[1],
2167         check_range=False).get()
2168 
2169     normalized_boxes_per_image = box_list_ops.clip_to_window(
2170         box_list.BoxList(normalized_boxes_per_image),
2171         tf.constant([0.0, 0.0, 1.0, 1.0], tf.float32),
2172         filter_nonoverlapping=False).get()
2173 
2174     if boxes_contains_classes_dim:
2175       max_num_proposals, num_classes, _ = (
2176           shape_utils.combined_static_and_dynamic_shape(
2177               boxes_and_image_shape[0]))
2178       normalized_boxes_per_image = shape_utils.expand_first_dimension(
2179           normalized_boxes_per_image, [max_num_proposals, num_classes])
2180 
2181     return normalized_boxes_per_image
2182 
2183   def loss(self, prediction_dict, true_image_shapes, scope=None):
2184     """Compute scalar loss tensors given prediction tensors.
2185 
2186     If number_of_stages=1, only RPN related losses are computed (i.e.,
2187     `rpn_localization_loss` and `rpn_objectness_loss`).  Otherwise all
2188     losses are computed.
2189 
2190     Args:
2191       prediction_dict: a dictionary holding prediction tensors (see the
2192         documentation for the predict method.  If number_of_stages=1, we
2193         expect prediction_dict to contain `rpn_box_encodings`,
2194         `rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background`, `rpn_features_to_crop`,
2195         `image_shape`, and `anchors` fields.  Otherwise we expect
2196         prediction_dict to additionally contain `refined_box_encodings`,
2197         `class_predictions_with_background`, `num_proposals`, and
2198         `proposal_boxes` fields.
2199       true_image_shapes: int32 tensor of shape [batch, 3] where each row is
2200         of the form [height, width, channels] indicating the shapes
2201         of true images in the resized images, as resized images can be padded
2202         with zeros.
2203       scope: Optional scope name.
2204 
2205     Returns:
2206       a dictionary mapping loss keys (`first_stage_localization_loss`,
2207         `first_stage_objectness_loss`, 'second_stage_localization_loss',
2208         'second_stage_classification_loss') to scalar tensors representing
2209         corresponding loss values.
2210     """
2211     with tf.name_scope(scope, 'Loss', prediction_dict.values()):
2212       (groundtruth_boxlists, groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
2213        groundtruth_masks_list, groundtruth_weights_list
2214       ) = self._format_groundtruth_data(
2215           self._image_batch_shape_2d(prediction_dict['image_shape']))
2216       loss_dict = self._loss_rpn(
2217           prediction_dict['rpn_box_encodings'],
2218           prediction_dict['rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background'],
2219           prediction_dict['anchors'], groundtruth_boxlists,
2220           groundtruth_classes_with_background_list, groundtruth_weights_list)
2221       if self._number_of_stages > 1:
2222         loss_dict.update(
2223             self._loss_box_classifier(
2224                 prediction_dict['refined_box_encodings'],
2225                 prediction_dict['class_predictions_with_background'],
2226                 prediction_dict['proposal_boxes'],
2227                 prediction_dict['num_proposals'], groundtruth_boxlists,
2228                 groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
2229                 groundtruth_weights_list, prediction_dict['image_shape'],
2230                 prediction_dict.get('mask_predictions'), groundtruth_masks_list,
2231                 prediction_dict.get(
2232                     fields.DetectionResultFields.detection_boxes),
2233                 prediction_dict.get(
2234                     fields.DetectionResultFields.num_detections)))
2235     return loss_dict
2236 
2237   def _loss_rpn(self, rpn_box_encodings,
2238                 rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background, anchors,
2239                 groundtruth_boxlists, groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
2240                 groundtruth_weights_list):
2241     """Computes scalar RPN loss tensors.
2242 
2243     Uses self._proposal_target_assigner to obtain regression and classification
2244     targets for the first stage RPN, samples a "minibatch" of anchors to
2245     participate in the loss computation, and returns the RPN losses.
2246 
2247     Args:
2248       rpn_box_encodings: A 3-D float tensor of shape
2249         [batch_size, num_anchors, self._box_coder.code_size] containing
2250         predicted proposal box encodings.
2251       rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background: A 2-D float tensor of shape
2252         [batch_size, num_anchors, 2] containing objectness predictions
2253         (logits) for each of the anchors with 0 corresponding to background
2254         and 1 corresponding to object.
2255       anchors: A 2-D tensor of shape [num_anchors, 4] representing anchors
2256         for the first stage RPN.  Note that `num_anchors` can differ depending
2257         on whether the model is created in training or inference mode.
2258       groundtruth_boxlists: A list of BoxLists containing coordinates of the
2259         groundtruth boxes.
2260       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list: A list of 2-D one-hot
2261         (or k-hot) tensors of shape [num_boxes, num_classes+1] containing the
2262         class targets with the 0th index assumed to map to the background class.
2263       groundtruth_weights_list: A list of 1-D tf.float32 tensors of shape
2264         [num_boxes] containing weights for groundtruth boxes.
2265 
2266     Returns:
2267       a dictionary mapping loss keys (`first_stage_localization_loss`,
2268         `first_stage_objectness_loss`) to scalar tensors representing
2269         corresponding loss values.
2270     """
2271     with tf.name_scope('RPNLoss'):
2272       (batch_cls_targets, batch_cls_weights, batch_reg_targets,
2273        batch_reg_weights, _) = target_assigner.batch_assign_targets(
2274            target_assigner=self._proposal_target_assigner,
2275            anchors_batch=box_list.BoxList(anchors),
2276            gt_box_batch=groundtruth_boxlists,
2277            gt_class_targets_batch=(len(groundtruth_boxlists) * [None]),
2278            gt_weights_batch=groundtruth_weights_list)
2279       batch_cls_weights = tf.reduce_mean(batch_cls_weights, axis=2)
2280       batch_cls_targets = tf.squeeze(batch_cls_targets, axis=2)
2281 
2282       def _minibatch_subsample_fn(inputs):
2283         cls_targets, cls_weights = inputs
2284         return self._first_stage_sampler.subsample(
2285             tf.cast(cls_weights, tf.bool),
2286             self._first_stage_minibatch_size, tf.cast(cls_targets, tf.bool))
2287       batch_sampled_indices = tf.cast(shape_utils.static_or_dynamic_map_fn(
2288           _minibatch_subsample_fn,
2289           [batch_cls_targets, batch_cls_weights],
2290           dtype=tf.bool,
2291           parallel_iterations=self._parallel_iterations,
2292           back_prop=True), dtype=tf.float32)
2293 
2294       # Normalize by number of examples in sampled minibatch
2295       normalizer = tf.maximum(
2296           tf.reduce_sum(batch_sampled_indices, axis=1), 1.0)
2297       batch_one_hot_targets = tf.one_hot(
2298           tf.cast(batch_cls_targets, dtype=tf.int32), depth=2)
2299       sampled_reg_indices = tf.multiply(batch_sampled_indices,
2300                                         batch_reg_weights)
2301 
2302       losses_mask = None
2303       if self.groundtruth_has_field(fields.InputDataFields.is_annotated):
2304         losses_mask = tf.stack(self.groundtruth_lists(
2305             fields.InputDataFields.is_annotated))
2306       localization_losses = self._first_stage_localization_loss(
2307           rpn_box_encodings, batch_reg_targets, weights=sampled_reg_indices,
2308           losses_mask=losses_mask)
2309       objectness_losses = self._first_stage_objectness_loss(
2310           rpn_objectness_predictions_with_background,
2311           batch_one_hot_targets,
2312           weights=tf.expand_dims(batch_sampled_indices, axis=-1),
2313           losses_mask=losses_mask)
2314       localization_loss = tf.reduce_mean(
2315           tf.reduce_sum(localization_losses, axis=1) / normalizer)
2316       objectness_loss = tf.reduce_mean(
2317           tf.reduce_sum(objectness_losses, axis=1) / normalizer)
2318 
2319       localization_loss = tf.multiply(self._first_stage_loc_loss_weight,
2320                                       localization_loss,
2321                                       name='localization_loss')
2322       objectness_loss = tf.multiply(self._first_stage_obj_loss_weight,
2323                                     objectness_loss, name='objectness_loss')
2324       loss_dict = {'Loss/RPNLoss/localization_loss': localization_loss,
2325                    'Loss/RPNLoss/objectness_loss': objectness_loss}
2326     return loss_dict
2327 
2328   def _loss_box_classifier(self,
2329                            refined_box_encodings,
2330                            class_predictions_with_background,
2331                            proposal_boxes,
2332                            num_proposals,
2333                            groundtruth_boxlists,
2334                            groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
2335                            groundtruth_weights_list,
2336                            image_shape,
2337                            prediction_masks=None,
2338                            groundtruth_masks_list=None,
2339                            detection_boxes=None,
2340                            num_detections=None):
2341     """Computes scalar box classifier loss tensors.
2342 
2343     Uses self._detector_target_assigner to obtain regression and classification
2344     targets for the second stage box classifier, optionally performs
2345     hard mining, and returns losses.  All losses are computed independently
2346     for each image and then averaged across the batch.
2347     Please note that for boxes and masks with multiple labels, the box
2348     regression and mask prediction losses are only computed for one label.
2349 
2350     This function assumes that the proposal boxes in the "padded" regions are
2351     actually zero (and thus should not be matched to).
2352 
2353 
2354     Args:
2355       refined_box_encodings: a 3-D tensor with shape
2356         [total_num_proposals, num_classes, box_coder.code_size] representing
2357         predicted (final) refined box encodings. If using a shared box across
2358         classes this will instead have shape
2359         [total_num_proposals, 1, box_coder.code_size].
2360       class_predictions_with_background: a 2-D tensor with shape
2361         [total_num_proposals, num_classes + 1] containing class
2362         predictions (logits) for each of the anchors.  Note that this tensor
2363         *includes* background class predictions (at class index 0).
2364       proposal_boxes: [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, 4] representing
2365         decoded proposal bounding boxes.
2366       num_proposals: A Tensor of type `int32`. A 1-D tensor of shape [batch]
2367         representing the number of proposals predicted for each image in
2368         the batch.
2369       groundtruth_boxlists: a list of BoxLists containing coordinates of the
2370         groundtruth boxes.
2371       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list: a list of 2-D one-hot
2372         (or k-hot) tensors of shape [num_boxes, num_classes + 1] containing the
2373         class targets with the 0th index assumed to map to the background class.
2374       groundtruth_weights_list: A list of 1-D tf.float32 tensors of shape
2375         [num_boxes] containing weights for groundtruth boxes.
2376       image_shape: a 1-D tensor of shape [4] representing the image shape.
2377       prediction_masks: an optional 4-D tensor with shape [total_num_proposals,
2378         num_classes, mask_height, mask_width] containing the instance masks for
2379         each box.
2380       groundtruth_masks_list: an optional list of 3-D tensors of shape
2381         [num_boxes, image_height, image_width] containing the instance masks for
2382         each of the boxes.
2383       detection_boxes: 3-D float tensor of shape [batch,
2384         max_total_detections, 4] containing post-processed detection boxes in
2385         normalized co-ordinates.
2386       num_detections: 1-D int32 tensor of shape [batch] containing number of
2387         valid detections in `detection_boxes`.
2388 
2389     Returns:
2390       a dictionary mapping loss keys ('second_stage_localization_loss',
2391         'second_stage_classification_loss') to scalar tensors representing
2392         corresponding loss values.
2393 
2394     Raises:
2395       ValueError: if `predict_instance_masks` in
2396         second_stage_mask_rcnn_box_predictor is True and
2397         `groundtruth_masks_list` is not provided.
2398     """
2399     with tf.name_scope('BoxClassifierLoss'):
2400       paddings_indicator = self._padded_batched_proposals_indicator(
2401           num_proposals, proposal_boxes.shape[1])
2402       proposal_boxlists = [
2403           box_list.BoxList(proposal_boxes_single_image)
2404           for proposal_boxes_single_image in tf.unstack(proposal_boxes)]
2405       batch_size = len(proposal_boxlists)
2406 
2407       num_proposals_or_one = tf.cast(tf.expand_dims(
2408           tf.maximum(num_proposals, tf.ones_like(num_proposals)), 1),
2409                                      dtype=tf.float32)
2410       normalizer = tf.tile(num_proposals_or_one,
2411                            [1, self.max_num_proposals]) * batch_size
2412 
2413       (batch_cls_targets_with_background, batch_cls_weights, batch_reg_targets,
2414        batch_reg_weights, _) = target_assigner.batch_assign_targets(
2415            target_assigner=self._detector_target_assigner,
2416            anchors_batch=proposal_boxlists,
2417            gt_box_batch=groundtruth_boxlists,
2418            gt_class_targets_batch=groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
2419            unmatched_class_label=tf.constant(
2420                [1] + self._num_classes * [0], dtype=tf.float32),
2421            gt_weights_batch=groundtruth_weights_list)
2422 
2423       class_predictions_with_background = tf.reshape(
2424           class_predictions_with_background,
2425           [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, -1])
2426 
2427       flat_cls_targets_with_background = tf.reshape(
2428           batch_cls_targets_with_background,
2429           [batch_size * self.max_num_proposals, -1])
2430       one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background = tf.argmax(
2431           flat_cls_targets_with_background, axis=1)
2432       one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background = tf.one_hot(
2433           one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background,
2434           flat_cls_targets_with_background.get_shape()[1])
2435 
2436       # If using a shared box across classes use directly
2437       if refined_box_encodings.shape[1] == 1:
2438         reshaped_refined_box_encodings = tf.reshape(
2439             refined_box_encodings,
2440             [batch_size, self.max_num_proposals, self._box_coder.code_size])
2441       # For anchors with multiple labels, picks refined_location_encodings
2442       # for just one class to avoid over-counting for regression loss and
2443       # (optionally) mask loss.
2444       else:
2445         reshaped_refined_box_encodings = (
2446             self._get_refined_encodings_for_postitive_class(
2447                 refined_box_encodings,
2448                 one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background, batch_size))
2449 
2450       losses_mask = None
2451       if self.groundtruth_has_field(fields.InputDataFields.is_annotated):
2452         losses_mask = tf.stack(self.groundtruth_lists(
2453             fields.InputDataFields.is_annotated))
2454       second_stage_loc_losses = self._second_stage_localization_loss(
2455           reshaped_refined_box_encodings,
2456           batch_reg_targets,
2457           weights=batch_reg_weights,
2458           losses_mask=losses_mask) / normalizer
2459       second_stage_cls_losses = ops.reduce_sum_trailing_dimensions(
2460           self._second_stage_classification_loss(
2461               class_predictions_with_background,
2462               batch_cls_targets_with_background,
2463               weights=batch_cls_weights,
2464               losses_mask=losses_mask),
2465           ndims=2) / normalizer
2466 
2467       second_stage_loc_loss = tf.reduce_sum(
2468           second_stage_loc_losses * tf.cast(paddings_indicator,
2469                                             dtype=tf.float32))
2470       second_stage_cls_loss = tf.reduce_sum(
2471           second_stage_cls_losses * tf.cast(paddings_indicator,
2472                                             dtype=tf.float32))
2473 
2474       if self._hard_example_miner:
2475         (second_stage_loc_loss, second_stage_cls_loss
2476         ) = self._unpad_proposals_and_apply_hard_mining(
2477             proposal_boxlists, second_stage_loc_losses,
2478             second_stage_cls_losses, num_proposals)
2479       localization_loss = tf.multiply(self._second_stage_loc_loss_weight,
2480                                       second_stage_loc_loss,
2481                                       name='localization_loss')
2482 
2483       classification_loss = tf.multiply(self._second_stage_cls_loss_weight,
2484                                         second_stage_cls_loss,
2485                                         name='classification_loss')
2486 
2487       loss_dict = {'Loss/BoxClassifierLoss/localization_loss':
2488                        localization_loss,
2489                    'Loss/BoxClassifierLoss/classification_loss':
2490                        classification_loss}
2491       second_stage_mask_loss = None
2492       if prediction_masks is not None:
2493         if groundtruth_masks_list is None:
2494           raise ValueError('Groundtruth instance masks not provided. '
2495                            'Please configure input reader.')
2496 
2497         if not self._is_training:
2498           (proposal_boxes, proposal_boxlists, paddings_indicator,
2499            one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background
2500           ) = self._get_mask_proposal_boxes_and_classes(
2501               detection_boxes, num_detections, image_shape,
2502               groundtruth_boxlists, groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
2503               groundtruth_weights_list)
2504         unmatched_mask_label = tf.zeros(image_shape[1:3], dtype=tf.float32)
2505         (batch_mask_targets, _, _, batch_mask_target_weights,
2506          _) = target_assigner.batch_assign_targets(
2507              target_assigner=self._detector_target_assigner,
2508              anchors_batch=proposal_boxlists,
2509              gt_box_batch=groundtruth_boxlists,
2510              gt_class_targets_batch=groundtruth_masks_list,
2511              unmatched_class_label=unmatched_mask_label,
2512              gt_weights_batch=groundtruth_weights_list)
2513 
2514         # Pad the prediction_masks with to add zeros for background class to be
2515         # consistent with class predictions.
2516         if prediction_masks.get_shape().as_list()[1] == 1:
2517           # Class agnostic masks or masks for one-class prediction. Logic for
2518           # both cases is the same since background predictions are ignored
2519           # through the batch_mask_target_weights.
2520           prediction_masks_masked_by_class_targets = prediction_masks
2521         else:
2522           prediction_masks_with_background = tf.pad(
2523               prediction_masks, [[0, 0], [1, 0], [0, 0], [0, 0]])
2524           prediction_masks_masked_by_class_targets = tf.boolean_mask(
2525               prediction_masks_with_background,
2526               tf.greater(one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background, 0))
2527 
2528         mask_height = shape_utils.get_dim_as_int(prediction_masks.shape[2])
2529         mask_width = shape_utils.get_dim_as_int(prediction_masks.shape[3])
2530         reshaped_prediction_masks = tf.reshape(
2531             prediction_masks_masked_by_class_targets,
2532             [batch_size, -1, mask_height * mask_width])
2533 
2534         batch_mask_targets_shape = tf.shape(batch_mask_targets)
2535         flat_gt_masks = tf.reshape(batch_mask_targets,
2536                                    [-1, batch_mask_targets_shape[2],
2537                                     batch_mask_targets_shape[3]])
2538 
2539         # Use normalized proposals to crop mask targets from image masks.
2540         flat_normalized_proposals = box_list_ops.to_normalized_coordinates(
2541             box_list.BoxList(tf.reshape(proposal_boxes, [-1, 4])),
2542             image_shape[1], image_shape[2], check_range=False).get()
2543 
2544         flat_cropped_gt_mask = self._crop_and_resize_fn(
2545             tf.expand_dims(flat_gt_masks, -1),
2546             tf.expand_dims(flat_normalized_proposals, axis=1),
2547             [mask_height, mask_width])
2548         # Without stopping gradients into cropped groundtruth masks the
2549         # performance with 100-padded groundtruth masks when batch size > 1 is
2550         # about 4% worse.
2551         # TODO(rathodv): Investigate this since we don't expect any variables
2552         # upstream of flat_cropped_gt_mask.
2553         flat_cropped_gt_mask = tf.stop_gradient(flat_cropped_gt_mask)
2554 
2555         batch_cropped_gt_mask = tf.reshape(
2556             flat_cropped_gt_mask,
2557             [batch_size, -1, mask_height * mask_width])
2558 
2559         mask_losses_weights = (
2560             batch_mask_target_weights * tf.cast(paddings_indicator,
2561                                                 dtype=tf.float32))
2562         mask_losses = self._second_stage_mask_loss(
2563             reshaped_prediction_masks,
2564             batch_cropped_gt_mask,
2565             weights=tf.expand_dims(mask_losses_weights, axis=-1),
2566             losses_mask=losses_mask)
2567         total_mask_loss = tf.reduce_sum(mask_losses)
2568         normalizer = tf.maximum(
2569             tf.reduce_sum(mask_losses_weights * mask_height * mask_width), 1.0)
2570         second_stage_mask_loss = total_mask_loss / normalizer
2571 
2572       if second_stage_mask_loss is not None:
2573         mask_loss = tf.multiply(self._second_stage_mask_loss_weight,
2574                                 second_stage_mask_loss, name='mask_loss')
2575         loss_dict[mask_loss.op.name] = mask_loss
2576     return loss_dict
2577 
2578   def _get_mask_proposal_boxes_and_classes(
2579       self, detection_boxes, num_detections, image_shape, groundtruth_boxlists,
2580       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list, groundtruth_weights_list):
2581     """Returns proposal boxes and class targets to compute evaluation mask loss.
2582 
2583     During evaluation, detection boxes are used to extract features for mask
2584     prediction. Therefore, to compute mask loss during evaluation detection
2585     boxes must be used to compute correct class and mask targets. This function
2586     returns boxes and classes in the correct format for computing mask targets
2587     during evaluation.
2588 
2589     Args:
2590       detection_boxes: A 3-D float tensor of shape [batch, max_detection_boxes,
2591         4] containing detection boxes in normalized co-ordinates.
2592       num_detections: A 1-D float tensor of shape [batch] containing number of
2593         valid boxes in `detection_boxes`.
2594       image_shape: A 1-D tensor of shape [4] containing image tensor shape.
2595       groundtruth_boxlists: A list of groundtruth boxlists.
2596       groundtruth_classes_with_background_list: A list of groundtruth classes.
2597       groundtruth_weights_list: A list of groundtruth weights.
2598     Return:
2599       mask_proposal_boxes: detection boxes to use for mask proposals in absolute
2600         co-ordinates.
2601       mask_proposal_boxlists: `mask_proposal_boxes` in a list of BoxLists in
2602         absolute co-ordinates.
2603       mask_proposal_paddings_indicator: a tensor indicating valid boxes.
2604       mask_proposal_one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background: Class targets
2605         computed using detection boxes.
2606     """
2607     batch, max_num_detections, _ = detection_boxes.shape.as_list()
2608     proposal_boxes = tf.reshape(box_list_ops.to_absolute_coordinates(
2609         box_list.BoxList(tf.reshape(detection_boxes, [-1, 4])), image_shape[1],
2610         image_shape[2]).get(), [batch, max_num_detections, 4])
2611     proposal_boxlists = [
2612         box_list.BoxList(detection_boxes_single_image)
2613         for detection_boxes_single_image in tf.unstack(proposal_boxes)
2614     ]
2615     paddings_indicator = self._padded_batched_proposals_indicator(
2616         tf.cast(num_detections, dtype=tf.int32), detection_boxes.shape[1])
2617     (batch_cls_targets_with_background, _, _, _,
2618      _) = target_assigner.batch_assign_targets(
2619          target_assigner=self._detector_target_assigner,
2620          anchors_batch=proposal_boxlists,
2621          gt_box_batch=groundtruth_boxlists,
2622          gt_class_targets_batch=groundtruth_classes_with_background_list,
2623          unmatched_class_label=tf.constant(
2624              [1] + self._num_classes * [0], dtype=tf.float32),
2625          gt_weights_batch=groundtruth_weights_list)
2626     flat_cls_targets_with_background = tf.reshape(
2627         batch_cls_targets_with_background, [-1, self._num_classes + 1])
2628     one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background = tf.argmax(
2629         flat_cls_targets_with_background, axis=1)
2630     one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background = tf.one_hot(
2631         one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background,
2632         flat_cls_targets_with_background.get_shape()[1])
2633     return (proposal_boxes, proposal_boxlists, paddings_indicator,
2634             one_hot_flat_cls_targets_with_background)
2635 
2636   def _get_refined_encodings_for_postitive_class(
2637       self, refined_box_encodings, flat_cls_targets_with_background,
2638       batch_size):
2639     # We only predict refined location encodings for the non background
2640     # classes, but we now pad it to make it compatible with the class
2641     # predictions
2642     refined_box_encodings_with_background = tf.pad(refined_box_encodings,
2643                                                    [[0, 0], [1, 0], [0, 0]])
2644     refined_box_encodings_masked_by_class_targets = (
2645         box_list_ops.boolean_mask(
2646             box_list.BoxList(
2647                 tf.reshape(refined_box_encodings_with_background,
2648                            [-1, self._box_coder.code_size])),
2649             tf.reshape(tf.greater(flat_cls_targets_with_background, 0), [-1]),
2650             use_static_shapes=self._use_static_shapes,
2651             indicator_sum=batch_size * self.max_num_proposals
2652             if self._use_static_shapes else None).get())
2653     return tf.reshape(
2654         refined_box_encodings_masked_by_class_targets, [
2655             batch_size, self.max_num_proposals,
2656             self._box_coder.code_size
2657         ])
2658 
2659   def _padded_batched_proposals_indicator(self,
2660                                           num_proposals,
2661                                           max_num_proposals):
2662     """Creates indicator matrix of non-pad elements of padded batch proposals.
2663 
2664     Args:
2665       num_proposals: Tensor of type tf.int32 with shape [batch_size].
2666       max_num_proposals: Maximum number of proposals per image (integer).
2667 
2668     Returns:
2669       A Tensor of type tf.bool with shape [batch_size, max_num_proposals].
2670     """
2671     batch_size = tf.size(num_proposals)
2672     tiled_num_proposals = tf.tile(
2673         tf.expand_dims(num_proposals, 1), [1, max_num_proposals])
2674     tiled_proposal_index = tf.tile(
2675         tf.expand_dims(tf.range(max_num_proposals), 0), [batch_size, 1])
2676     return tf.greater(tiled_num_proposals, tiled_proposal_index)
2677 
2678   def _unpad_proposals_and_apply_hard_mining(self,
2679                                              proposal_boxlists,
2680                                              second_stage_loc_losses,
2681                                              second_stage_cls_losses,
2682                                              num_proposals):
2683     """Unpads proposals and applies hard mining.
2684 
2685     Args:
2686       proposal_boxlists: A list of `batch_size` BoxLists each representing
2687         `self.max_num_proposals` representing decoded proposal bounding boxes
2688         for each image.
2689       second_stage_loc_losses: A Tensor of type `float32`. A tensor of shape
2690         `[batch_size, self.max_num_proposals]` representing per-anchor
2691         second stage localization loss values.
2692       second_stage_cls_losses: A Tensor of type `float32`. A tensor of shape
2693         `[batch_size, self.max_num_proposals]` representing per-anchor
2694         second stage classification loss values.
2695       num_proposals: A Tensor of type `int32`. A 1-D tensor of shape [batch]
2696         representing the number of proposals predicted for each image in
2697         the batch.
2698 
2699     Returns:
2700       second_stage_loc_loss: A scalar float32 tensor representing the second
2701         stage localization loss.
2702       second_stage_cls_loss: A scalar float32 tensor representing the second
2703         stage classification loss.
2704     """
2705     for (proposal_boxlist, single_image_loc_loss, single_image_cls_loss,
2706          single_image_num_proposals) in zip(
2707              proposal_boxlists,
2708              tf.unstack(second_stage_loc_losses),
2709              tf.unstack(second_stage_cls_losses),
2710              tf.unstack(num_proposals)):
2711       proposal_boxlist = box_list.BoxList(
2712           tf.slice(proposal_boxlist.get(),
2713                    [0, 0], [single_image_num_proposals, -1]))
2714       single_image_loc_loss = tf.slice(single_image_loc_loss,
2715                                        [0], [single_image_num_proposals])
2716       single_image_cls_loss = tf.slice(single_image_cls_loss,
2717                                        [0], [single_image_num_proposals])
2718       return self._hard_example_miner(
2719           location_losses=tf.expand_dims(single_image_loc_loss, 0),
2720           cls_losses=tf.expand_dims(single_image_cls_loss, 0),
2721           decoded_boxlist_list=[proposal_boxlist])
2722 
2723   def regularization_losses(self):
2724     """Returns a list of regularization losses for this model.
2725 
2726     Returns a list of regularization losses for this model that the estimator
2727     needs to use during training/optimization.
2728 
2729     Returns:
2730       A list of regularization loss tensors.
2731     """
2732     all_losses = []
2733     slim_losses = tf.get_collection(tf.GraphKeys.REGULARIZATION_LOSSES)
2734     # Copy the slim losses to avoid modifying the collection
2735     if slim_losses:
2736       all_losses.extend(slim_losses)
2737     # TODO(kaftan): Possibly raise an error if the feature extractors are
2738     # uninitialized in Keras.
2739     if self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features:
2740       if (self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features !=
2741           _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR):
2742         all_losses.extend(self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features.losses)
2743     if isinstance(self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv,
2744                   tf.keras.Model):
2745       all_losses.extend(
2746           self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv.losses)
2747     if self._first_stage_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
2748       all_losses.extend(self._first_stage_box_predictor.losses)
2749     if self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features:
2750       if (self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features !=
2751           _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR):
2752         all_losses.extend(
2753             self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features.losses)
2754     if self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor:
2755       if self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
2756         all_losses.extend(self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.losses)
2757     return all_losses
2758 
2759   def restore_map(self,
2760                   fine_tune_checkpoint_type='detection',
2761                   load_all_detection_checkpoint_vars=False):
2762     """Returns a map of variables to load from a foreign checkpoint.
2763 
2764     See parent class for details.
2765 
2766     Args:
2767       fine_tune_checkpoint_type: whether to restore from a full detection
2768         checkpoint (with compatible variable names) or to restore from a
2769         classification checkpoint for initialization prior to training.
2770         Valid values: `detection`, `classification`. Default 'detection'.
2771        load_all_detection_checkpoint_vars: whether to load all variables (when
2772          `fine_tune_checkpoint_type` is `detection`). If False, only variables
2773          within the feature extractor scopes are included. Default False.
2774 
2775     Returns:
2776       A dict mapping variable names (to load from a checkpoint) to variables in
2777       the model graph.
2778     Raises:
2779       ValueError: if fine_tune_checkpoint_type is neither `classification`
2780         nor `detection`.
2781     """
2782     if fine_tune_checkpoint_type not in ['detection', 'classification']:
2783       raise ValueError('Not supported fine_tune_checkpoint_type: {}'.format(
2784           fine_tune_checkpoint_type))
2785     if fine_tune_checkpoint_type == 'classification':
2786       return self._feature_extractor.restore_from_classification_checkpoint_fn(
2787           self.first_stage_feature_extractor_scope,
2788           self.second_stage_feature_extractor_scope)
2789 
2790     variables_to_restore = variables_helper.get_global_variables_safely()
2791     variables_to_restore.append(tf.train.get_or_create_global_step())
2792     # Only load feature extractor variables to be consistent with loading from
2793     # a classification checkpoint.
2794     include_patterns = None
2795     if not load_all_detection_checkpoint_vars:
2796       include_patterns = [
2797           self.first_stage_feature_extractor_scope,
2798           self.second_stage_feature_extractor_scope
2799       ]
2800     feature_extractor_variables = slim.filter_variables(
2801         variables_to_restore, include_patterns=include_patterns)
2802     return {var.op.name: var for var in feature_extractor_variables}
2803 
2804   def updates(self):
2805     """Returns a list of update operators for this model.
2806 
2807     Returns a list of update operators for this model that must be executed at
2808     each training step. The estimator's train op needs to have a control
2809     dependency on these updates.
2810 
2811     Returns:
2812       A list of update operators.
2813     """
2814     update_ops = []
2815     slim_update_ops = tf.get_collection(tf.GraphKeys.UPDATE_OPS)
2816     # Copy the slim ops to avoid modifying the collection
2817     if slim_update_ops:
2818       update_ops.extend(slim_update_ops)
2819     # Passing None to get_updates_for grabs updates that should always be
2820     # executed and don't depend on any model inputs in the graph.
2821     # (E.g. if there was some count that should be incremented every time a
2822     # model is run).
2823     #
2824     # Passing inputs grabs updates that are transitively computed from the
2825     # model inputs being passed in.
2826     # (E.g. a batchnorm update depends on the observed inputs)
2827     if self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features:
2828       if (self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features !=
2829           _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR):
2830         update_ops.extend(
2831             self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features.get_updates_for(None))
2832         update_ops.extend(
2833             self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features.get_updates_for(
2834                 self._feature_extractor_for_proposal_features.inputs))
2835     if isinstance(self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv,
2836                   tf.keras.Model):
2837       update_ops.extend(
2838           self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv.get_updates_for(
2839               None))
2840       update_ops.extend(
2841           self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv.get_updates_for(
2842               self._first_stage_box_predictor_first_conv.inputs))
2843     if self._first_stage_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
2844       update_ops.extend(
2845           self._first_stage_box_predictor.get_updates_for(None))
2846       update_ops.extend(
2847           self._first_stage_box_predictor.get_updates_for(
2848               self._first_stage_box_predictor.inputs))
2849     if self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features:
2850       if (self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features !=
2851           _UNINITIALIZED_FEATURE_EXTRACTOR):
2852         update_ops.extend(
2853             self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features.get_updates_for(
2854                 None))
2855         update_ops.extend(
2856             self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features.get_updates_for(
2857                 self._feature_extractor_for_box_classifier_features.inputs))
2858     if self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor:
2859       if self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.is_keras_model:
2860         update_ops.extend(
2861             self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.get_updates_for(None))
2862         update_ops.extend(
2863             self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.get_updates_for(
2864                 self._mask_rcnn_box_predictor.inputs))
2865     return update_ops
